{"title_page": "Colopene", "text_new": "'''Colopene''' or '''Culupene''' or '''Calupene''' ([[Greek language|Greek]]: \u039a\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5\u03c0\u03b7\u03bd\u03ae), was an ancient district in [[Kingdom of Pontus|Pontus]] on the border of [[Armenia Minor]].<ref>{{Cite Strabo|p. 560}}</ref> [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]] places [[Sivas, Turkey|Sebastia]] (modern Sivas) and [[Sulusaray|Sebastopolis]] (modern Sulusaray) in Colopene.<ref>{{Cite Pliny|6.3}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{SmithDGRG|title=Colopene}}\n\n[[Category:Pontus]]\n\n{{ancientGreece-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Colopene''' or '''Culupene''' or '''Calupene''' ([[Greek language|Greek]]: \u039a\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5\u03c0\u03b7\u03bd\u03ae), was an ancient district in [[Kingdom of Pontus|Pontus]] on the border of [[Armenia Minor]].<ref>{{Cite Strabo|p. 560}}</ref> [[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]] places [[Sivas, Turkey|Sebastia]] (modern Sivas) and [[Sulusaray|Sebastopolis]] (modern Sulusaray) in Colopene.<ref>{{Cite Pliny|6.3}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{SmithDGRG|title=Colopene}}\n\n[[Category:Pontus]]\n[[Category:Historical regions of Anatolia]]\n\n{{ancientGreece-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Mugsalot", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Historical regions of AnatoliausingHotCatRemoved grandparent category", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colopene"}
{"title_page": "Alain Fuchs", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix  = \n| name              = Alain Fuchs\n| honorific_suffix  =\n| native_name       = \n| native_name_lang  = \n| image             = Alain Fuchs 2018 (2).jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_upright     = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = Alain Fuchs in 2018\n| birth_date        = {{b-da|10 April 1953}}\n| birth_place       = [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]]\n| death_date        = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)-->\n| death_place       = \n| death_cause       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}-->\n| other_names       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = [[French people|French]]\n| fields            = [[Physical Chemistry]]\n| workplaces        = {{ublist |[[PSL Research University]] |[[Centre national de la recherche scientifique]] |[[University of Paris-Sud]] |[[Chimie ParisTech]] |[[Universit\u00e9 Pierre-et-Marie-Curie]]}}\n| patrons           = \n| education         = [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique F\u00e9d\u00e9rale de Lausanne]]\n| alma_mater        = \n| thesis_title      = <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url        = <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year       = <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor  = Henri Szwarc\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| spouse            = <!--(or | spouses = )-->\n| partner           = <!--(or | partners = )-->\n| children          = \n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''Alain Fuchs''' (born 10 April 1953) is a Swiss-born French [[Doctor of Science]] and chemistry [[Professor]], specialized in molecular simulation. He is also university administrator. He served as the president of [[Chimie ParisTech]] from 2006 to 2010. He has served as the president of the [[French National Centre for Scientific Research]] from 2010 to 2017.<ref name=\"lemondeunnouveaupatron\">{{cite news|last1=Jacqu\u00e9|first1=Philippe|title=Un nouveau patron pour le CNRS|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2010/01/14/un-nouveau-patron-pour-le-cnrs_1291882_3224.html|accessdate=April 3, 2016|work=Le Monde|date=January 14, 2010}}</ref>{{'}}<ref>{{cite news|title= Anne Peyroche est nomm\u00e9e pr\u00e9sidente du CNRS par int\u00e9rim |url= http://www2.cnrs.fr/presse/communique/5275.htm |work= CNRS |date= October 24, 2017 |accessdate= 24 October 2017}}</ref> He became an Officer of the [[Legion of Honour]] in 2014.<ref name=\"journalofficiel\">{{cite journal|title=ORDRE NATIONAL DU M\u00c9RITE|journal=Journal Officiel de la R\u00e9publique Fran\u00e7aise|date=May 15, 2014|url=http://www.legiondhonneur.fr/sites/default/files/onm_20140515.pdf|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSince 24 October 2017, he is president of [[PSL Research University]] (Paris Sciences & Lettres).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.univ-psl.fr/en/actualites/alain-fuchs-elected-president-psl|title=Alain Fuchs elected president of PSL {{!}} PSL|website=www.univ-psl.fr|language=en|access-date=2017-10-09}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nAlain Fuchs graduated as a Chemical engineer (1975) at [[EPFL]].<ref name=Educpro/> In 1983, he became a doctor in Physical Chemistry at [[Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud]]; his dissertation was \u201cCristaux vitreux et transition vitreuse\u201d (about glass crystals).<ref>Alain Fuchs ''Cristaux vitreux et transition vitreuse'' - [[Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud]] - 1983 \u2013 Doctoral advisor : Henri Szwarc  - Dissertation number: 1983PA112380 - [http://www.sudoc.fr/043134777 SUDOC website] - Worldcat : 490643197</ref> He was also a postdoctoral fellow at the [[University of Edinburgh]] (1984\u20131985).<ref>{{cite web|language=French|url=http://www.industrie-techno.com/alain-fuchs-un-pedagogue-a-la-tete-du-cnrs.36343|author=Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Preveraud|date=2015-02-18 |website=Industrie&technologies|title=Alain Fuchs, un p\u00e9dagogue \u00e0 la t\u00eate du CNRS|accessdate=2015-04-23}}</ref>\n\n=== Career ===\nAlain Fuchs joined CNRS in 1985 as a research fellow. He became a research director in 1991. In 1995, he became chemistry professor at Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud. Between 2000 and 2005, he set up and directed the Laboratory of Physic Chemistry (UMR 8000) at Campus d'Orsay. He also worked as the President of the [[agr\u00e9gation]] in chemistry from 1998 to 2001 and he directed the Section 13 of the Comit\u00e9 national de la recherche scientifique between 2004 and 2008. He was also Professor at the [[Universit\u00e9 Pierre et Marie Curie]] (UPMC) in thermodynamics and statistical thermodynamics, intermolecular and surface forces, molecular simulation techniques, history of chemistry and physical chemistry. He served as the president of Chimie ParisTech from 2006 to 2010.<ref name=Educpro />\n\nIn January 2010, he was appointed President of the CNRS, succeeding Catherine Br\u00e9chignac (former President) d'Arnold Migus (former managing director).<ref name=\"monde2101\">{{cite news|language=French|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2010/01/21/alain-fuchs-une-nouvelle-chimie-pour-le-cnrs_1294851_3224.html|author=Philippe Jacqu\u00e9|title=Alain Fuchs : une nouvelle chimie pour le CNRS|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=2010-01-21}}</ref>{{,}}<ref name=commCNRS>{{cite web|language=French|url=http://www2.cnrs.fr/presse/communique/1772.htm|title=Communiqu\u00e9 - Alain Fuchs est nomm\u00e9 pr\u00e9sident du CNRS|website=CNRS|date=2010-01-20|accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>{{,}}<ref>D\u00e9cret du 21 janvier 2010 portant nomination du pr\u00e9sident du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00018 du 22 janvier 2010 page 1427, texte n\u00b0 90</ref> Fuchs\u2019s mandate ended in 2014. After holding the position in interim for one month],<ref>{{in lang|fr}} Arr\u00eat\u00e9 du 10 janvier 2014 portant attribution de fonctions au Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00013 du 16 janvier 2014 page 760 texte n\u00b0 46</ref> he was appointed again by the Ministry of Higher Education.<ref>{{in lang|fr}} D\u00e9cret du 27 f\u00e9vrier 2014 portant nomination du pr\u00e9sident du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00050 du 28 f\u00e9vrier 2014 page 3943 texte n\u00b0 112</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, Fuchs quit the position of CNRS President and became the President of [[PSL Research University|Universit\u00e9 PSL]] (collegiate university including 9 members and 10 associate members).\n\n== Fields of research ==\nHis research activity is dedicated to the theory, modelling and molecular thermodynamics of fluids confined in various types of porous materials modeling and molecular simulation of confined fluids.<ref name=Educpro>{{cite web|language=french|author=Educpro|title=Alain Fuchs: Biography|year=2017|url=https://www.letudiant.fr/educpros/personnalites/fuchs-alain-325.html}}</ref> \u201cForced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices\u201d<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Guillaume Fraux|author2=Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert|author3=Anne Boutin|author4=Alain Fuchs|title=Forced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices|journal=[[Chem. Soc. Rev.]]|issue=46|pages=7421\u20137437|year=2017}}</ref> ([[Chem. Soc. Rev.]],46 (2017)) or \u201cOn the use of the IAST method for gas separation studies in porous materials with gate-opening behavior\u201d<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Thomas D. Bennett|author2= Anthony K. Cheetham|author3= Alain H. Fuchs|author4= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert|title=Interplay between defects, disorder and flexibility in metal-organic frameworks|journal=Nature Chemistry|year=2017|issue=9|pages=11\u201316}}</ref> (Adsorption, 24 (2018)) are part of his last recent and major publications.\n\nAlain Fuchs is a member of the [[Academia Europaea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ae-info.org/ae/User/Fuchs_Alain|title=Alain H. Fuchs|website=Academia Europaea|access-date=2015-03-23}}</ref> and he was a member of the editorial board of the journal ''[[Physical Chemistry Chemical Physics]]''.\n\nHe co-authored two books: \n* {{cite book|language=French|author1= Anne Boutin | author2= Gilberte Dosseh | author3= Alain Fuchs |title=\u00c9l\u00e9ments de thermodynamique. Cours et exercices corrig\u00e9s pour le deuxi\u00e8me cycle de chimie, chimie-physique et sciences physiques|publisher=Elsevier Masson|year=1997}}\n* {{cite book | language=French|author1=Georges Bram| author2= Fran\u00e7oise Chamozzi| author3= Alain Fuchs| author4=Andr\u00e9 Grelon| author5=Caroline Lanciano-Morandat| author6=Laurence Mordenti|title=La Chimie dans la soci\u00e9t\u00e9. Son r\u00f4le, son image|publisher=L\u2019Harmattan|year=1995}}\n\n=== Major works ===\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anne Boutin |author2=Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3= Guillaume Fraux |author4=Alain Fuchs|title=Forced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices|journal=[[Chem. Soc. Rev.]]|issue=46|pages=7421\u20137437|year=2017}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Thomas D. Bennett|author2= Anthony K. Cheetham |author3= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author4= Alain Fuchs |title=Interplay between defects, disorder and flexibility in metal-organic frameworks|journal=[[Nature Chemistry]]|year=2017|issue=9|pages=11\u201316}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author2= Alain Fuchs |title= Computational characterization and prediction of metal-organic framework properties|journal= Coordination Chemistry Reviews|issue=307|year=2016|pages=2011\u2013236}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Thomas D. Bennett | author2= Anthony K. Cheetham | author3= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert| author4= Alain Fuchs |title= Flexibility and disorder in metal-organic frameworks |journal= [[Dalton Transactions]]|issue=45|year=2016|page=4058}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Aur\u00e9lie U. Ortiz |title= Anisotropic elastic properties of flexible metal-organic frameworks: how soft are soft porous crystals? |journal= [[Physical Review Letters]] |issue=109|year=2012|page=195502}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Alexander V. Neimark|title= Stress-based model for the \" breathing \" of metal-organic frameworks |journal= [[Journal of Physical Chemistry Letters]]|issue=1|year=2010|page=445 }}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois\u2010Xavier Coudert |author3= Gerard Ferey |author4= Alain Fuchs|author5= Antoine Gedeon | author6= Thierry Loiseau |author7= Andrei Nossov | author8= Marie\u2010Anne Springuel\u2010Huet | author9= Christophe Volkringer |title= Breathing transitions in MIL-53(Al) Metal-Organic Framework upon xenon adsorption |journal= [[Angewandte Chemie International Edition]]|issue=48|year=2009|page=8314}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anne Boutin |author2= Fran\u00e7ois\u2010Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Marie Jeffroy|author5= Caroline Mellot-Draznieks| title= Thermodynamics of guest-induced structural transitions in hybrid organic-inorganic frameworks |journal= [[Journal of the American Chemical Society]]|issue=130|year=2008|page=14294}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fabien Cailliez|author3= Isabelle Demachy |author4=Alain Fuchs|author5= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author6= Michel Soulard |author7= Mickael Trzpit |title= Thermodynamics of water intrusion in nanoporous hydrophobic solids |journal= [[Physical Chemistry Chemical Physics]] (Cover article)|issue=10|year=2008|page=4817}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fabien Cailliez|author3= Isabelle Demachy |author4= Nicolas Desbiens |author5= Alain Fuchs |author6= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author7= Michel Soulard |author8= Mickael Trzpit | title= The effect of local defects on water adsorption in silicalite-1 zeolite. A joint experimental and molecular simulation study |journal= [[Langmuir (journal)|Langmuir]]|issue=23|year=2007|page=10131}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Isabelle Demachy |author2= Nicolas Desbiens |author3= Alain Fuchs |author4= Hel\u00e8ne Kirsch\u2010Rodeschini |author5= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author6 = Michel Soulard | title= Water condensation in hydrophobic nanopores |journal= Angewandte Chemie International Edition |issue=44|year=2005|page=5310}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anthony K. Cheetham |author2=Alain Fuchs |title= Adsorption of guest molecules in zeolitic materials: computational aspects |journal= [[The Journal of Physical Chemistry B]]|issue=105|year=2001|page=7375}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Christele Beauvais |author2= Anne Boutin|author3=Jerome Delhommelle | author4=Alain Fuchs|author5=Bernard Rousseau|author6= Philippe Ungerer| title= Optimization of the anisotropic united atoms intermolecular potential for n-alkanes |journal= [[Journal of Chemical Physics]] |issue=112|year=2000|page=5499}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2=Alain Fuchs|author3=Jean-Bernard Maillet|title= Numerical evidence of an embryonic orientational phase transition in small nitrogen clusters |journal= [[Physical Review Letters]]|issue=76|year=1996|page=4336}}\n\n== Honors and awards ==\n* Knight of [[Palmes acad\u00e9miques]] (1996)\n* [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry]] (2006)\n* Knight of the [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur]] (2010)<ref>{{in lang|fr}} D\u00e9cret du 13 juillet 2010 portant promotion et nomination, JORF n\u00b00161 du 14 juillet 2010 page 13049, texte n\u00b0 4</ref>\n* Officer of the [[National Order of Merit (France)|National Order of Merit]] (2014)<ref name=decretmerite>{{cite web|language=French|title=Ordre national du m\u00e9rite - d\u00e9cret du 14 mai 2014|url = http://www.legiondhonneur.fr/sites/default/files/onm_20140515.pdf|website=L\u00e9gion d'honneur|date=2014-05-15|accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>\n* Officer of the [[National Order of Quebec]] (2014)<ref>{{cite web|language=French|title=Alain Fuchs re\u00e7oit les insignes d\u2019Officier de l\u2019Ordre national du Qu\u00e9bec des mains du Premier Ministre du Qu\u00e9bec|url=http://www.cnrs.fr/derci/spip.php?article827|website=CNRS|date=2014-11-07|accessdate=2015-04-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Alain Fuchs}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fuchs, Alain}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lausanne]]\n[[Category:French academics]]\n[[Category:French chemists]]\n[[Category:Officiers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix  = \n| name              = Alain Fuchs\n| honorific_suffix  =\n| native_name       = \n| native_name_lang  = \n| image             = Alain Fuchs 2018 (2).jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_upright     = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = Alain Fuchs in 2018\n| birth_date        = {{b-da|10 April 1953}}\n| birth_place       = [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]]\n| death_date        = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD |YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)-->\n| death_place       = \n| death_cause       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!--{{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}}-->\n| other_names       = \n| residence         = \n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = [[French people|French]]\n| fields            = [[Physical Chemistry]]\n| workplaces        = {{ublist |[[PSL Research University]] |[[Centre national de la recherche scientifique]] |[[University of Paris-Sud]] |[[Chimie ParisTech]] |[[Universit\u00e9 Pierre-et-Marie-Curie]]}}\n| patrons           = \n| education         = [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique F\u00e9d\u00e9rale de Lausanne]]\n| alma_mater        = \n| thesis_title      = <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url        = <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year       = <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor  = Henri Szwarc\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| spouse            = <!--(or | spouses = )-->\n| partner           = <!--(or | partners = )-->\n| children          = \n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\n'''Alain Fuchs''' (born 10 April 1953) is a Swiss-born French [[Doctor of Science]] and chemistry [[Professor]], specialized in molecular simulation. He is also university administrator. He served as the president of [[Chimie ParisTech]] from 2006 to 2010. He has served as the president of the [[French National Centre for Scientific Research]] from 2010 to 2017.<ref name=\"lemondeunnouveaupatron\">{{cite news|last1=Jacqu\u00e9|first1=Philippe|title=Un nouveau patron pour le CNRS|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2010/01/14/un-nouveau-patron-pour-le-cnrs_1291882_3224.html|accessdate=April 3, 2016|work=Le Monde|date=January 14, 2010}}</ref>{{'}}<ref>{{cite news|title= Anne Peyroche est nomm\u00e9e pr\u00e9sidente du CNRS par int\u00e9rim |url= http://www2.cnrs.fr/presse/communique/5275.htm |work= CNRS |date= October 24, 2017 |accessdate= 24 October 2017}}</ref> He became an Officer of the [[Legion of Honour]] in 2014.<ref name=\"journalofficiel\">{{cite journal|title=ORDRE NATIONAL DU M\u00c9RITE|journal=Journal Officiel de la R\u00e9publique Fran\u00e7aise|date=May 15, 2014|url=http://www.legiondhonneur.fr/sites/default/files/onm_20140515.pdf|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nSince 24 October 2017, he is president of [[PSL Research University]] (Paris Sciences & Lettres).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.univ-psl.fr/en/actualites/alain-fuchs-elected-president-psl|title=Alain Fuchs elected president of PSL {{!}} PSL|website=www.univ-psl.fr|language=en|access-date=2017-10-09}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nAlain Fuchs graduated as a Chemical engineer (1975) at [[EPFL]].<ref name=Educpro/> In 1983, he became a doctor in Physical Chemistry at [[Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud]]; his dissertation was \u201cCristaux vitreux et transition vitreuse\u201d (about glass crystals).<ref>Alain Fuchs ''Cristaux vitreux et transition vitreuse'' - [[Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud]] - 1983 \u2013 Doctoral advisor : Henri Szwarc  - Dissertation number: 1983PA112380 - [http://www.sudoc.fr/043134777 SUDOC website] - Worldcat : 490643197</ref> He was also a postdoctoral fellow at the [[University of Edinburgh]] (1984\u20131985).<ref>{{cite web|language=French|url=http://www.industrie-techno.com/alain-fuchs-un-pedagogue-a-la-tete-du-cnrs.36343|author=Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Preveraud|date=2015-02-18 |website=Industrie&technologies|title=Alain Fuchs, un p\u00e9dagogue \u00e0 la t\u00eate du CNRS|accessdate=2015-04-23}}</ref>\n\n=== Career ===\nAlain Fuchs joined CNRS in 1985 as a research fellow. He became a research director in 1991. In 1995, he became chemistry professor at Universit\u00e9 Paris-Sud. Between 2000 and 2005, he set up and directed the Laboratory of Physic Chemistry (UMR 8000) at Campus d'Orsay. He also worked as the President of the [[agr\u00e9gation]] in chemistry from 1998 to 2001 and he directed the Section 13 of the Comit\u00e9 national de la recherche scientifique between 2004 and 2008. He was also Professor at the [[Universit\u00e9 Pierre et Marie Curie]] (UPMC) in thermodynamics and statistical thermodynamics, intermolecular and surface forces, molecular simulation techniques, history of chemistry and physical chemistry. He served as the president of Chimie ParisTech from 2006 to 2010.<ref name=Educpro />\n\nIn January 2010, he was appointed President of the CNRS, succeeding Catherine Br\u00e9chignac (former President) d'Arnold Migus (former managing director).<ref name=\"monde2101\">{{cite news|language=French|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/societe/article/2010/01/21/alain-fuchs-une-nouvelle-chimie-pour-le-cnrs_1294851_3224.html|author=Philippe Jacqu\u00e9|title=Alain Fuchs : une nouvelle chimie pour le CNRS|newspaper=[[Le Monde]]|date=2010-01-21}}</ref>{{,}}<ref name=commCNRS>{{cite web|language=French|url=http://www2.cnrs.fr/presse/communique/1772.htm|title=Communiqu\u00e9 - Alain Fuchs est nomm\u00e9 pr\u00e9sident du CNRS|website=CNRS|date=2010-01-20|accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>{{,}}<ref>D\u00e9cret du 21 janvier 2010 portant nomination du pr\u00e9sident du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00018 du 22 janvier 2010 page 1427, texte n\u00b0 90</ref> Fuchs\u2019s mandate ended in 2014. After holding the position in interim for one month],<ref>{{in lang|fr}} Arr\u00eat\u00e9 du 10 janvier 2014 portant attribution de fonctions au Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00013 du 16 janvier 2014 page 760 texte n\u00b0 46</ref> he was appointed again by the Ministry of Higher Education.<ref>{{in lang|fr}} D\u00e9cret du 27 f\u00e9vrier 2014 portant nomination du pr\u00e9sident du Centre national de la recherche scientifique, JORF n\u00b00050 du 28 f\u00e9vrier 2014 page 3943 texte n\u00b0 112</ref>\n\nIn October 2017, Fuchs quit the position of CNRS President and became the President of [[PSL Research University|Universit\u00e9 PSL]] (collegiate university including 9 membres and 10 associate members).\n\n== Fields of research ==\nHis research activity is dedicated to the theory, modelling and molecular thermodynamics of fluids confined in various types of porous materials modeling and molecular simulation of confined fluids.<ref name=Educpro>{{cite web|language=french|author=Educpro|title=Alain Fuchs: Biography|year=2017|url=https://www.letudiant.fr/educpros/personnalites/fuchs-alain-325.html}}</ref> \u201cForced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices\u201d<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Guillaume Fraux|author2=Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert|author3=Anne Boutin|author4=Alain Fuchs|title=Forced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices|journal=[[Chem. Soc. Rev.]]|issue=46|pages=7421\u20137437|year=2017}}</ref> ([[Chem. Soc. Rev.]],46 (2017)) or \u201cOn the use of the IAST method for gas separation studies in porous materials with gate-opening behavior\u201d<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Thomas D. Bennett|author2= Anthony K. Cheetham|author3= Alain H. Fuchs|author4= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert|title=Interplay between defects, disorder and flexibility in metal-organic frameworks|journal=Nature Chemistry|year=2017|issue=9|pages=11\u201316}}</ref> (Adsorption, 24 (2018)) are part of his last recent and major publications.\n\nAlain Fuchs is a member of the [[Academia Europaea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ae-info.org/ae/User/Fuchs_Alain|title=Alain H. Fuchs|website=Academia Europaea|access-date=2015-03-23}}</ref> and he was a member of the editorial board of the journal ''[[Physical Chemistry Chemical Physics]]''.\n\nHe co-authored two books: \n* {{cite book|language=French|author1= Anne Boutin | author2= Gilberte Dosseh | author3= Alain Fuchs |title=\u00c9l\u00e9ments de thermodynamique. Cours et exercices corrig\u00e9s pour le deuxi\u00e8me cycle de chimie, chimie-physique et sciences physiques|publisher=Elsevier Masson|year=1997}}\n* {{cite book | language=French|author1=Georges Bram| author2= Fran\u00e7oise Chamozzi| author3= Alain Fuchs| author4=Andr\u00e9 Grelon| author5=Caroline Lanciano-Morandat| author6=Laurence Mordenti|title=La Chimie dans la soci\u00e9t\u00e9. Son r\u00f4le, son image|publisher=L\u2019Harmattan|year=1995}}\n\n=== Major works ===\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anne Boutin |author2=Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3= Guillaume Fraux |author4=Alain Fuchs|title=Forced intrusion of water and aqueous solutions in microporous materials: from fundamental thermodynamics to energy storage devices|journal=[[Chem. Soc. Rev.]]|issue=46|pages=7421\u20137437|year=2017}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Thomas D. Bennett|author2= Anthony K. Cheetham |author3= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author4= Alain Fuchs |title=Interplay between defects, disorder and flexibility in metal-organic frameworks|journal=[[Nature Chemistry]]|year=2017|issue=9|pages=11\u201316}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author2= Alain Fuchs |title= Computational characterization and prediction of metal-organic framework properties|journal= Coordination Chemistry Reviews|issue=307|year=2016|pages=2011\u2013236}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Thomas D. Bennett | author2= Anthony K. Cheetham | author3= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert| author4= Alain Fuchs |title= Flexibility and disorder in metal-organic frameworks |journal= [[Dalton Transactions]]|issue=45|year=2016|page=4058}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Aur\u00e9lie U. Ortiz |title= Anisotropic elastic properties of flexible metal-organic frameworks: how soft are soft porous crystals? |journal= [[Physical Review Letters]] |issue=109|year=2012|page=195502}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois-Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Alexander V. Neimark|title= Stress-based model for the \" breathing \" of metal-organic frameworks |journal= [[Journal of Physical Chemistry Letters]]|issue=1|year=2010|page=445 }}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fran\u00e7ois\u2010Xavier Coudert |author3= Gerard Ferey |author4= Alain Fuchs|author5= Antoine Gedeon | author6= Thierry Loiseau |author7= Andrei Nossov | author8= Marie\u2010Anne Springuel\u2010Huet | author9= Christophe Volkringer |title= Breathing transitions in MIL-53(Al) Metal-Organic Framework upon xenon adsorption |journal= [[Angewandte Chemie International Edition]]|issue=48|year=2009|page=8314}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anne Boutin |author2= Fran\u00e7ois\u2010Xavier Coudert |author3=Alain Fuchs|author4= Marie Jeffroy|author5= Caroline Mellot-Draznieks| title= Thermodynamics of guest-induced structural transitions in hybrid organic-inorganic frameworks |journal= [[Journal of the American Chemical Society]]|issue=130|year=2008|page=14294}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fabien Cailliez|author3= Isabelle Demachy |author4=Alain Fuchs|author5= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author6= Michel Soulard |author7= Mickael Trzpit |title= Thermodynamics of water intrusion in nanoporous hydrophobic solids |journal= [[Physical Chemistry Chemical Physics]] (Cover article)|issue=10|year=2008|page=4817}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2= Fabien Cailliez|author3= Isabelle Demachy |author4= Nicolas Desbiens |author5= Alain Fuchs |author6= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author7= Michel Soulard |author8= Mickael Trzpit | title= The effect of local defects on water adsorption in silicalite-1 zeolite. A joint experimental and molecular simulation study |journal= [[Langmuir (journal)|Langmuir]]|issue=23|year=2007|page=10131}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Isabelle Demachy |author2= Nicolas Desbiens |author3= Alain Fuchs |author4= Hel\u00e8ne Kirsch\u2010Rodeschini |author5= Jo\u00ebl Patarin |author6 = Michel Soulard | title= Water condensation in hydrophobic nanopores |journal= Angewandte Chemie International Edition |issue=44|year=2005|page=5310}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Anthony K. Cheetham |author2=Alain Fuchs |title= Adsorption of guest molecules in zeolitic materials: computational aspects |journal= [[The Journal of Physical Chemistry B]]|issue=105|year=2001|page=7375}}\n* {{cite journal|author1= Christele Beauvais |author2= Anne Boutin|author3=Jerome Delhommelle | author4=Alain Fuchs|author5=Bernard Rousseau|author6= Philippe Ungerer| title= Optimization of the anisotropic united atoms intermolecular potential for n-alkanes |journal= [[Journal of Chemical Physics]] |issue=112|year=2000|page=5499}}\n* {{cite journal|author1=Anne Boutin|author2=Alain Fuchs|author3=Jean-Bernard Maillet|title= Numerical evidence of an embryonic orientational phase transition in small nitrogen clusters |journal= [[Physical Review Letters]]|issue=76|year=1996|page=4336}}\n\n== Honors and awards ==\n* Knight of [[Palmes acad\u00e9miques]] (1996)\n* [[Fellow of the Royal Society of Chemistry]] (2006)\n* Knight of the [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur]] (2010)<ref>{{in lang|fr}} D\u00e9cret du 13 juillet 2010 portant promotion et nomination, JORF n\u00b00161 du 14 juillet 2010 page 13049, texte n\u00b0 4</ref>\n* Officer of the [[National Order of Merit (France)|National Order of Merit]] (2014)<ref name=decretmerite>{{cite web|language=French|title=Ordre national du m\u00e9rite - d\u00e9cret du 14 mai 2014|url = http://www.legiondhonneur.fr/sites/default/files/onm_20140515.pdf|website=L\u00e9gion d'honneur|date=2014-05-15|accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>\n* Officer of the [[National Order of Quebec]] (2014)<ref>{{cite web|language=French|title=Alain Fuchs re\u00e7oit les insignes d\u2019Officier de l\u2019Ordre national du Qu\u00e9bec des mains du Premier Ministre du Qu\u00e9bec|url=http://www.cnrs.fr/derci/spip.php?article827|website=CNRS|date=2014-11-07|accessdate=2015-04-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Alain Fuchs}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fuchs, Alain}}\n[[Category:1953 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lausanne]]\n[[Category:French academics]]\n[[Category:French chemists]]\n[[Category:Officiers of the L\u00e9gion d'honneur]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alain_Fuchs"}
