 (association football)|defender]] for [[Gamba Osaka]] in the Japanese [[J1 League]].\n\nA strong and physical centre\u2013back defender, Shoji is capable of covering and positioning using speed, as well as, his increase strength and intensity of one on one.<ref name=\"Shoji2\">{{cite web|url=https://news.biglobe.ne.jp/sports/1105/fot_151105_2180420237.html|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u6b21\u4e16\u4ee3\u62c5\u3046\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3002\"\u5e38\u52dd\u8ecd\u56e3\"\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u3001\u82e5\u304dDF\u30ea\u30fc\u30c0\u30fc\u304c\u80cc\u8ca0\u3046\u4f7f\u547d\u611f\u3068\u899a\u609f|publisher=Big Globe|language=Japanese|date=5 November 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407154029/https://news.biglobe.ne.jp/sports/1105/fot_151105_2180420237.html|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji3\">{{cite web|url=https://qoly.jp/player/worldchampionship/profile/700-762-2174-17503|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90|publisher=Qoly Football|language=Japanese|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150129031826/https://qoly.jp/player/worldchampionship/profile/700-762-2174-17503|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=[Y\u2606voice_36]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u30d8\u30c7\u30a3\u30f3\u30b0\u306f\u8ab0\u306b\u3082\u8ca0\u3051\u305f\u304f\u306a\u3044\u3001\u81ea\u4fe1\u304c\u3042\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?72916-61806-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 August 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u304c\u540dDF\u3092\u8f29\u51fa\u3057\u7d9a\u3051\u308b\u7406\u7531--\u79cb\u7530\u8c4a\u00d7\u4e2d\u7530\u6d69\u30cb\u00d7\u660c\u5b50\u6e90|url=https://logmi.jp/business/articles/40520|publisher=Logmi Biz|language=Japanese|date=19 February 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Kashima Antlers===\nBorn in [[Kobe]], Japan, Sh\u014dji started playing football when he was two years old, starting out in a forward position.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\"/> His performance when he was in fourth grade playing against the sixth grade attracted attention from Fresca Kobe U12 (Hyogo Prefecture), who signed him.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/clubs/shoji-gen.html|title=\u80cc\u756a\u53f73\u306e\u91cd\u307f\u3002\u6311\u6226\u306f\u7d9a\u304f\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161219035637/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/clubs/shoji-gen.html|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He joined Gamba Osaka Junior Youth during middle school and then Yonago Kita High School.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=[j\u9ad8\u6821\u7dcf\u4f53]\u4f50\u8cc0\u6771vs\u7c73\u5b50\u5317 \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?57829-40488-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=7 August 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u9ad8\u6821\u7dcf\u4f53]\u5927\u4f1a\u512a\u79c0\u9078\u624b\u306b\u897f\u6fa4\u3001\u8c37\u5c3e\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u3001\u98a8\u9593\u5144\u3089|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?57893-40586-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 August 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u5168\u65e5\u672c\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9(U-18)\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u5f37\u529b\u3060\u3063\u305f\"\u30dc\u30fc\u30eb\u72e9\u308a\"\u30682\u30c8\u30c3\u30d7\u3001\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u304c\u9759\u5b66\u6c88\u3081\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59054-42201-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u5168\u65e5\u672c\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9(U-18)\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u3001\u9ad8\u901f\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u3067\u5343\u8449U-18\u7c89\u7815|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59639-43037-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> While at Yonago Kita High School, Shoji switched to playing in the centre\u2013back position, a position he played today.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u9ad8\u6821MOM_62]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u9ad8DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90(2\u5e74)_\u5148\u767a\u596a\u53d6\u534a\u5e74\u306eCB\u304c\u8105\u5a01\u306b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59055-42202-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u300cY\u2606voice_13\u300d\u7c73\u5b50\u5317DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9\u3082\u610f\u8b58\u3057\u3066\u3044\u304f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?69327-56668-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=27 May 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56386?static=true|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\uff5e\u7a81\u7136\u8a00\u308f\u308c\u305f\u3001\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u3078\u306e\u8ee2\u5411\uff5e|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=24 December 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322212819/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56386?static=true|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u306e\u300c\u4f1d\u8aac\u300d\u3002\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u6311\u3080CB\u3078\u3001\u5f8c\u8f29\u305f\u3061\u304c\u30a8\u30fc\u30eb\u300c\u660c\u5b50\u9078\u624b\u306a\u3089\u7d76\u5bfe\u306b\u6b62\u3081\u3066\u304f\u308c\u308b\u306f\u305a\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?247467-247467-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At first, Shoji was unhappy with the team\u2019s decision to switch him into the centre\u2013back position, but over time, he accepted playing in the position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56387?static=true|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\uff5e\u4e00\u5bfe\u4e00\u306f\u7d76\u5bfe\u306b\u8ca0\u3051\u306a\u3044\uff5e|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 December 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322212833/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56387?static=true|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50&\u5869\u8c37\u304c\u300eNIKEiD\u300f\u3067\u611b\u7528\u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30af\u3092\u81ea\u5206\u597d\u307f\u306b\u30c7\u30b6\u30a4\u30f3|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?186890-186890-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 April 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced on 30 September 2010 that Shoji would be joining [[Kashima Antlers]] from 1 January 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/8865|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u9078\u624b\u306e2011\u5e74\u52a0\u5165\u5185\u5b9a\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=30 September 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321230600/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/8865|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Ahead of the 2011 season, Shoji was registered to the Kashima Antlers\u2019 first team in January.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/9734|title=2011\u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f3\u306e\u767b\u9332\u9078\u624b\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=1 February 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321230638/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/9734|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He spoke about his expectations at his new club, saying: \"In 2011, I want to work hard without losing, so that the directors and supporters can recognize me. I want to try out what I can do. I want to do my best to help my team.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u67f4\u5d0e\u3089J\u52a0\u5165\u5185\u5b9a\u9078\u624b\u300c2011\u5e74\u65b0\u5e74\u306e\u8a93\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78653-70275-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 January 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u30fb\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u6b63\u5f0f\u5951\u7d04\u3002\u300c\u81ea\u5206\u304c\u3069\u3053\u307e\u3067\u3067\u304d\u308b\u304b\u8a66\u3057\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79570-71503-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=21 January 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> He first appeared in the first team for Kashima Antlers as an unused substitute, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings]] in the AFC Champions League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/521|title=AFC\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30d4\u30aa\u30f3\u30ba\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c3|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 April 2013|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321231251/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/521|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> From that moment on, Shoji spent months on the substitute bench, due to [[Daiki Iwamasa]], [[Takeshi Aoki]] and [[Masahiko Inoha]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5ca9\u653f&\u4f0a\u91ce\u6ce2\u306e\u4ee3\u8868CB\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u306b\u6311\u3080\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u300cFK\u3082\u72d9\u3044\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?80162-72315-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 February 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u9023\u6226\u898b\u636e\u3048\u3066\u4e3b\u529b\u6e29\u5b58\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u3082\u521d\u306e\u30d9\u30f3\u30c1\u5165\u308a\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?83638-77471-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u4eca\u590f\u306eDF\u88dc\u5f37\u306f\u884c\u308f\u305a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?87139-81977-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 July 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 12 October 2011 when he made his Kashima Antlers debut, starting the whole game, in a 2\u20130 win against [[University of Tsukuba]] in the second round of the J. League Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/668|title=\u7530\u4ee3\u3001\u5927\u8feb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u7b51\u6ce2\u5927\u3092\u6483\u7834\u3002\u9806\u5f53\u306a3\u56de\u6226\u9032\u51fa\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=12 October 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321231400/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/668|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A month later on 16 November 2011 against [[Kataller Toyama]], Shoji made another appearance for the side, playing 62 minutes, in a 2\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/669|title=\u307e\u305f\u3057\u3066\u3082120\u5206\u9593\u306e\u6226\u3044\u3002\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5ef6\u9577\u6226\u3092\u5236\u30574\u56de\u6226\u9032\u51fa|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=15 November 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321232140/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/669|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2011 season, Shoji made two appearances for the side.\n\nIn the 2012 season, Shoji continued to remain on the substitute bench, as Iwamasa and Aoki were the first choice centre\u2013backs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/953|title=\u5f8c\u534a3\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u521d\u52dd\u5229\uff01\u3053\u308c\u3067\u30ab\u30b7\u30de\u901a\u7b97200\u52dd\u9054\u6210\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=21 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151539/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/953|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/958|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc! 7-0\u3068\u672d\u5e4c\u306b\u5927\u52dd!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=19 May 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322150808/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/958|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50143|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u30c9\u30a5\u30c8\u30e9\u3001\u5927\u8feb\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u57f7\u5ff5\u306e\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc! 2\u5e74\u9023\u7d9a\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=13 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322143931/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50143|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 24 March 2012 when he made his first appearance of the season, coming on as a 76th minutes substitute, in a 2\u20130 loss against [[Sanfrecce Hiroshima]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/949|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u958b\u5e553\u6226\u3067\u7121\u5f97\u70b9\u3001\u3044\u307e\u3060\u52dd\u5229\u306a\u3057\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=24 March 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151357/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/949|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A month later, Shoji made his first start of the season, playing in the centre\u2013back position, as he helped Kashima Antlers beat [[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo]] in the J.League Group Stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c10\u4eba\u306e\u672d\u5e4c\u306b\u7d42\u4e86\u9593\u969b\u306e\u5287\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?98151-98525-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> Over the season, Shoji then played in different positions, such as, defensive midfield, left\u2013back and right\u2013back, but most of them were substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/950|title=\u307e\u305f\u3082\u30ce\u30fc\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u306a\u304c\u3089\u3001\u52dd\u70b91\u3002\u524d\u9014\u306b\u304b\u3059\u304b\u306a\u5e0c\u671b\u306e\u5149\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151357/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/950|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/952|title=\u9060\u85e4\u306e\u5287\u7684\u6c7a\u52dd\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c2-1\u3068\u4eca\u5b63\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u521d\u52dd\u5229\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=14 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151359/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/952|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/986|title=\u5927\u8feb\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u3001\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229!! \u524d\u56de\u8987\u8005\u306e\u610f\u5730\u3092\u898b\u305b\u308b\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 June 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322150755/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/986|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/974|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc! \u30c9\u30a5\u30c8\u30e9\u306e\u521d\u30cf\u30c3\u30c8\u30c8\u30ea\u30c3\u30af\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u306e\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067FC\u6771\u4eac\u306b5-1\u306e\u5727\u52dd!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322143939/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/974|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 8 September 2012 when he scored his first Kashima Antlers\u2019 goal, in a 7\u20131 win against [[University of Tsukuba]] in the second round of the Emperor\u2019s Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50135|title=\u9060\u85e4\u306e3\u767a\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u516c\u5f0f\u6226\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u306a\u3069\u30677-1\u3068\u7b51\u6ce2\u5927\u3092\u6483\u7834!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=8 September 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121558/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50135|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Two months later on 3 November 2012, Shoji started in the left\u2013back position for the [[2012 J.League Cup Final|J.League Cup Final]] against [[Shimizu S-Pulse]] and played 83 minutes before being substituted, as Kashima Antlers won 2\u20131, his first title of his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50152|title=J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u6c7a\u52dd\u30c8\u30fc\u30ca\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8 \u6c7a\u52dd|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2012|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121551/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50152|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/freaksplus/20150715/todays-player.html|title=\u4eca\u65e5\u306e\u6ce8\u76ee\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u30e4\u30fc\u306f\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172833/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/freaksplus/20150715/todays-player.html|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After the match, Manager [[Jorginho (footballer, born 1964)|Jorginho]] evaluated his performance.<ref>{{cite news|title=19\u6b73\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u5927\u524d\u3092\u5fb9\u5e95\u30de\u30fc\u30af\u3001\u6307\u63ee\u5b98\u306e\u6307\u793a\u306f\u300c\u540c\u3058\u6c34\u3092\u98f2\u3093\u3067\u3082\u3044\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?106972-109304-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2012|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2012 season, he went on to make eighteen appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2013 season, Shoji made his first appearance of the season, coming on as a 77th minutes substitute, in a 3\u20132 win against [[Vegalta Sendai]] on 9 March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50171|title=2013\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c2\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=9 March 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121858/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50171|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, his first team opportunities was limited, due to competitions from Iwamasa, Aoki and new signing, [[Takanori Maeno]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5ca9\u653f\u51fa\u5834\u505c\u6b62\u3067\u5c71\u6751\u3089\u82e5\u624b\u306b\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30b9|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/p-sc-tp1-20130426-1117831.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 April 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9ce5\u6816vs\u9e7f\u5cf6 \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?111381-114602-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 March 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6vs\u9ce5\u6816 \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?112788-116328-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 April 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Despite this, Shoji made his first league start, starting the whole game, in a 3\u20132 win against [[FC Tokyo]] on 25 May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/games/50285/match_review|title= 2013\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c13\u7bc0 FC\u6771\u4eac\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=25 May 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323212153/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/games/50285/match_review|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By June, he suffered a meniscus damage while training and was sidelined for four months, eventually ruling him out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3011\u660c\u5b50\u306f\u534a\u6708\u677f\u640d\u50b7\u3000\u5168\u6cbb\u7d04\uff14\u30ab\u6708|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/f-sc-tp1-20130620-1145208.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji3\"/> Despite this, Shoji went on to make five appearances for the side at the end of the 2013 season.\n\nIn the 2014 season, Shoji returned to the starting line-up against [[Ventforet Kofu]] in the opening game of the season and scored from a header, in a 4\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51436/live|title= 2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c1\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=1 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310131618/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51436/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> This was followed up by helping the side keep two clean sheets in the next two matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50690|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c2\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=8 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125718/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50690|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51068/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c3\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=14 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323214958/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51068/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> His contribution to the first team helped the side finished at the top of the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51082/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c5\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323215337/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51082/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51124|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c9\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=26 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125738/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51124|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51129|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c10\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125740/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51129|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, as the season progressed, the club\u2019s place at the top of the table soon slipped.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51161|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c14\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=17 May 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221011/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51161|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50940|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c30\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=26 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323222148/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50940|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51341|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c34\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323222145/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51341|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By September, Shoji scored his second goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Omiya Ardija]] on 13 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50876|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c23\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=13 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221550/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50876|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> This was followed by keeping three clean sheets in the next three matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50885|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c24\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=20 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221601/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50885|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/45299|title=J1 \u7b2c25\u7bc0 \u30d9\u30ac\u30eb\u30bf\u4ed9\u53f0\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=23 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221555/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/45299|archivedate= 28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50907/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c26\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221552/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50907/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> The 2014 season proved to be Shoji\u2019s breakthrough to the Kashima Anthlers\u2019 first team, and cemented his place in the centre\u2013back position.<ref name=\"Shoji3\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u30d5\u30a9\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u5bfe\u7b56\u300c\u3055\u3055\u3084\u304d\u6226\u8853\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/p-sc-tp1-20140323-1274163.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30012014\u88dc\u5f37\u8a3a\u65ad\u3002\u6226\u529b\u4e0a\u7a4d\u307f\u306a\u304f\u3001\u540d\u9580\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u5927\u304d\u306a\u4e0d\u5b89|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2014/02/15/post26423/3/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=15 February 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the season, he went on to make forty appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2015 season, Shoji made his AFC Champions League debut, starting the whole game, as Kashima Anthlers lost 1\u20130 against [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a6\u30a7\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u30b7\u30c9\u30cb\u30fc\u3001ACL\u521d\u6226\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3092\u4e0b\u3059\uff08\u9ad8\u8429\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u52d5\u753b\u3042\u308a\uff09|url=https://qoly.jp/2015/02/25/acl-gl1-kashima-wsw|publisher=Qoly Football|language=Japanese|date=25 February 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he fractured his hand and was sidelined for weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u5de6\u624b\u9aa8\u6298\u306e\u624b\u8853|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1443939.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=8 March 2015|date=8 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 22 March 2015 when Shoji returned to the starting line-up, starting the whole game, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Nagoya Grampus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/48093|title=J1 1st \u7b2c3\u7bc0 vs \u540d\u53e4\u5c4b|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=22 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323224256/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/48093|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> Since returning to the first team, he continued to regain his first team place for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4eca\u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f3\u521d\u5b8c\u5c01\u306e\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u3053\u306e\u30bc\u30ed\u3092\u6a5f\u306b\u3001\u4f55\u304b\u304c\u5909\u308f\u3063\u305f\u3068\u601d\u3046\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?162786-162786-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051\u3092\u6094\u3084\u3080\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u3082\u3063\u3068\u3082\u3063\u3068\u5411\u4e0a\u3067\u304d\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?163647-163647-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= 3\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u306e\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c2\u4f4d\u3082\u6700\u4e0b\u4f4d\u3082\u4e00\u7dd2\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?175181-175181-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u6b21\u4e16\u4ee3\u62c5\u3046\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3002\"\u5e38\u52dd\u8ecd\u56e3\"\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u3001\u82e5\u304dDF\u30ea\u30fc\u30c0\u30fc\u304c\u80cc\u8ca0\u3046\u4f7f\u547d\u611f\u3068\u899a\u609f|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2015/11/05/post118219/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=5 November 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30015\u5e74\u9593\u306e\u6b74\u4ee3\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30e1\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30022\u51a0&\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u5236\u8987\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3082\u2026\u9060\u3056\u304b\u308b\u56fd\u5185\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u306e\u9053|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/03/19/post367437/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji2\"/> It wasn\u2019t until on 29 April 2015 when Shoji scored his first goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against Vegalta Sendai.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51559|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c8\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030022816/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51559|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By mid\u2013May, he began to play in the left\u2013back position from May to June.<ref name=\"Shoji4\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51575/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c13\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324171450/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51575/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51577/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c14\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=30 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172759/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51577/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51581/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c16\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172828/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51581/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 11 July 2015 when Shoji scored his second goal of the season, in a 3\u20132 win against [[Albirex Niigata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5f8c\u534aAT\u306e\u30c9\u30e9\u30de!!94\u5206\u304b\u3089\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u65b0\u6f5f\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u3061|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?166974-166974-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Two weeks later on 25 July 2015, he scored his third goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against [[FC Tokyo]]<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5fa9\u5e30\u306e\u67f4\u5d0e\u304c1G1A\u3067\u5b58\u5728\u611f\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u77f3\u4e95\u4f53\u5236\u521d\u9663\u3092\u767d\u661f\u3067\u98fe\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?167972-167972-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji  suffered an injury in the 20th minutes and had to be substitute during a 2\u20132 draw against FC Tokyo in the quarter\u2013finals of the J. League Cup first leg.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6cb3\u91ce\u3001\u4e2d\u5cf6\u304c\u30a2\u30d9\u30c3\u30af\u5f3e\u3082\u2026F\u6771\u4eac\u306f\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u5206\u3051\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?171041-171041-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 September 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 26 September 2015 when he made his return from injury, starting the whole match, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Urawa Red Diamonds]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u66fd\u30f6\u7aef\u304c\u307e\u3055\u304b\u306e\u30dd\u30ed\u30ea\u2026\u6d66\u548c\u3001\u8208\u68a0\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u5f3e\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229!!|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?172777-172777-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> A month later, Shoji played in both legs against [[Vissel Kobe]] in the semi\u2013finals of the J.League Cup and helped the side reach the final after winning 6\u20132 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51699/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u6c7a\u52dd\u30c8\u30fc\u30ca\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8 \u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd \u7b2c1\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=7 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324175036/https://www.so-net