ww.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51788|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After serving a one match suspension, he made his return to the starting line-up, as Kashima Antlers lost 3\u20131 loss against Gamba Osaka on 2 July 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u7b2c1S\u5236\u8987!! \u5c71\u672c&\u571f\u5c45\u5f3e\u30676\u9023\u52dd\u30d5\u30a3\u30cb\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?192555-192555-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7b2c1S\u8987\u8005\u304c\u521d\u306e3\u5931\u70b9\u3067\u9ed2\u661f\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u7518\u3055\u304c\u7d50\u679c\u306b\u51fa\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?193134-193134-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 July 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji continued to help the side remain at the top of the table for the next eleven matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=1st\u738b\u8005\u30fb\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c3\u767a\u5b8c\u5c01\u30672\u9023\u52dd\u2026\u82e6\u3057\u3080\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u300111\u6226\u52dd\u3061\u306a\u3057|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20160713/467993.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=13 July 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u62265\u8a66\u5408\u3076\u308a\u306e\u52dd\u5229\u2026\u8d64\u5d0e\u306e\u9bae\u3084\u304b\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u5f3e\u306a\u3069\u3067\u798f\u5ca1\u3092\u4e0b\u3059|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20160814/479849.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=14 August 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u5ddd\u5d0e\u304c\u6d66\u548c\u3068\u306e\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfe\u6c7a\u5236\u3057\u3066\u9996\u4f4d\u518d\u6d6e\u4e0a\u2026\u6e58\u5357\u306f\u6ce5\u6cbc7\u9023\u6557\uff0fJ1\u30fb2nd\u7b2c9\u7bc0|url=http://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20160820/482220.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=20 August 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 16 September 2016 when he scored his second goal of the season, in a 3\u20130 win against [[J\u00fabilo Iwata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u53f3SH\u3067\u5148\u767a\u306e\u67f4\u5d0e\u5cb3\u304c2\u70b9\u306b\u7d61\u3080! \u78d0\u7530\u306b3\u767a\u5b8c\u5c01\u306e\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c3\u6226\u3076\u308a\u767d\u661f|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?198849-198849-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 September 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At some point around this month, he signed a contract with the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uff27\u5927\u962a\u304c\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u7372\u5f97\u3078\u3000\u4e0b\u90e8\u7d44\u7e54\u3067\u5b87\u4f50\u7f8e\u540c\u671f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1728492.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=24 October 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Following the club\u2019s qualification to finish third place at the end of the J.League second stage, Shoji later helped the club win the league after playing both legs to beat [[Urawa Red Diamonds]] 2\u20132 on aggregate through away goal.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff13\u9023\u6557\u3082\u53ce\u7a6b\u3000\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u624b\u5fdc\u3048\u304b\u306a\u308a\u611f\u3058\u3066\u3044\u308b\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1731041.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=29 October 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= J\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30d4\u30aa\u30f3\u30b7\u30c3\u30d7\u6c7a\u52dd\u306f\u6d66\u548c\u304c\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306b\u5148\u52dd|url=https://news.livedoor.com/article/detail/12349446/|publisher=Livedoor News|language=Japanese|date=29 November 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u9006\u8ee2\u3067\u6d66\u548c\u4e0b\u3057\"\u4e0b\u514b\u4e0aV\"\uff01\u30007\u5e74\u3076\u308a8\u5ea6\u76ee\u306eJ1\u5236\u8987\u9054\u6210|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20161203/523060.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=3 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji played all the four matches in the [[2016 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]], as he helped Kashima Antlers reached the [[2016 FIFA Club World Cup Final|final]], only to lose 4\u20132 against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u9006\u8ee2\u3067\u30aa\u30fc\u30af\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u6483\u7834\uff0f\u30af\u30e9\u30d6\uff37\u676f\u958b\u5e55\u6226\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1748850.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=8 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u52e2\u521d\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa\uff0f\u30af\u30e9\u30d6\uff37\u676f\u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1751523.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\uff23\u30ed\u30ca\uff13\u767a\u3067\u30ec\u30a2\u30eb\u304c\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\uff0f\u30af\u30e9\u30d6\uff37\u676f\u6c7a\u52dd\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1753272.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=18 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji also helped the club reach the [[2016_Emperor%27s_Cup#Final|Emperor\u2019s Cup Final]] by beating [[Kawasaki Frontale]] 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30b2\u30ad\u3064\u3088\u3063!!vol.5\u300c\u969b\u7acb\u3063\u305f\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u5b8c\u6210\u5ea6\u3002\u61b2\u525b\u306f\u30ec\u30b8\u30a7\u30f3\u30c9\u306e\u5883\u5730\u3078\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?206691-206691-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=31 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff36\u3000\u30d9\u30c6\u30e9\u30f3\u82e5\u624b\u304c\u878d\u5408\u2026\u9ec4\u91d1\u6642\u4ee3\u518d\u6765\u306e\u4e88\u611f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1759867.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2016 season, he went on to make forty\u2013five appearances and scoring two times in all competitions. For his performance in the 2016 season, Shoji was named [[J.League Best XI]].<ref>{{cite news|title=J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30d9\u30b9\u30c811\u767a\u8868\uff01\u67cf\u6728\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u5c0f\u6797\u60a0\u3089\u304c\u521d\u9078\u51fa\u2026\u6700\u591a\u306f\u6d66\u548c\u306e4\u540d|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20161220/529696.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=20 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3001\u6fc0\u52d5\u306e1\u30f6\u6708\u3067\u5b66\u3073\u3068\u3063\u305f\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u4f1d\u7d71\u3002\u300c\u300e\u3044\u3044\u8a66\u5408\u3092\u3057\u305f\u300f\u3058\u3083\u3042\u610f\u5473\u304c\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2016/12/21/post191059/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=21 December 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2017 season, Shoji started the whole match against Urawa Red Diamonds in the [[2017 Japanese Super Cup|Japanese Super Cup]], as he helped Kashima Antlers win 3\u20132 to win the trophy.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u76f8\u624b\u306e\u30df\u30b9\u304c\u306a\u3051\u308c\u3070\u2026\u52dd\u3063\u3066\u515c\u306e\u7dd2\u3092\u7de0\u3081\u308b\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u9006\u8ee2\u3055\u308c\u308b\u30e0\u30fc\u30c9\u3060\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?209787-209787-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 February 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji then helped the side kept three clean sheets in three matches between 4 March 2017 and 14 March 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6c7a\u52dd\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u52dd\u5229\u306b\u8ca2\u732e\u3057\u305f\u9e7f\u5cf6MF\u30ec\u30aa\u30fb\u30b7\u30eb\u30d0\u300c\u30a4\u30e1\u30fc\u30b8\u