4e0a\u304c\u308c\u305a\u202620\u51a0\u76ee\u524d\u3067V\u9038\u3001\u5e38\u52dd\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306b\u30d7\u30ec\u30c3\u30b7\u30e3\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?232287-232287-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Following this, Shoji said he was determined to help the club win a trophy next season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e21\u65b9\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3057\u305f\u9078\u624b\u306f\u5f37\u304f\u306a\u308b\u2026DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u512a\u52dd\u306b\u5c0e\u3051\u308b\u9078\u624b\u306b\u306a\u308a\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://news.livedoor.com/article/detail/13987956/|publisher=News Live Door|language=Japanese|date=5 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> For his performance in the 2017 season, Shoji was named J.League Best XI for the second time in his career.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5c0f\u6797\u60a0\u304cMVP\u521d\u53d7\u8cde!!J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30a2\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30ba\u3067\u30d9\u30b9\u30c811\u306a\u3069\u5404\u8cde\u3092\u8868\u5f70|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?232585-232585-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Having played every matches at the end of the 2017 season,<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4e21\u65b9\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3057\u305f\u9078\u624b\u306f\u5f37\u304f\u306a\u308b\u2026DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u512a\u52dd\u306b\u5c0e\u3051\u308b\u9078\u624b\u306b\u306a\u308a\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?232601-232601-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9996\u4f4d\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff24\uff26\u753a\u7530\u300c\u6bcd\u306e\u65e5\u300d\u306b\u521d\u5148\u767a\u521d\u51fa\u5834\u52dd\u5229\u3092|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1822802.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=13 May 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9996\u4f4d\u8d70\u308b\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306f\u30ab\u30fc\u30d7\uff01\u9ed2\u7530\u7684\u5c0f\u7b20\u539f\u3001\u65b0\u4e95\u7684\u66fd\u30b1\u7aef|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201709170000088.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=17 September 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji went on to make forty\u2013six appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\n[[File:Kashima Antlers lifted 2018 ACL trophy.jpg|thumb|left|400px|Shoji lifting the AFC Champions League trophy following a 2\u20130 win on aggregate against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]].]]\n\nIn the 2018 season, Shoji helped Kashima Antlers kept two clean sheets in the first two league matches of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff27\uff2b\u30b9\u30f3\u30c6\u597d\u5b88\u3067\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\u3001\u5185\u7530\u300c\u9996\u306e\u76ae\u4e00\u679a\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201802250000665.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 February 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u91d1\u5d0e\uff36\u5f3e\u3001\u653b\u5b88\u306b\u5b58\u5728\u611f\u306e\u5c0f\u7b20\u539f\u306b\u300c\u5168\u7136\u9055\u3046\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201803030000783.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He then captained the side for the next three matches between on 13 March 2018 and 31 March 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30d7\u30ed\u521d\u5148\u767a\u306e19\u6b73\u5c0f\u7530\u304c\u5148\u5236\u70b9\u6f14\u51fa\u3082\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306f\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u8ffd\u3044\u3064\u304b\u308c\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?239649-239649-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\uff2a\uff11\u9ce5\u6816\u3001\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5727\u5012\u3057\u305f\u306e\u306b\u2026\u521d\u9ed2\u661f\u3000\u30d5\u30a3\u30c3\u30ab\u30c7\u30f3\u30c6\u30a3\u76e3\u7763\u306f\u624b\u5fdc\u3048|url=https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/nsp/item/n/402132/|publisher=Nishi Nippon|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u672d\u5e4c\u3068\u3082\u306b\u597d\u6a5f\u751f\u304b\u305b\u305a\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u672d\uff15\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201803310001094.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji suffered a calf injury that saw him missed two matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u76e3\u7763\u300c\u3084\u308b\u3079\u304d\u3053\u3068\u3084\u3063\u3066\u304f\u308c\u305f\u300d\u9078\u624b\u306b\u611f\u8b1d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804040000005.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=4 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 14 April 2018 when he made his return to the starting line-up from injury, in a 2\u20130 win against Nagoya Grampus.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u91d1\u5d0e\uff12\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u6ce5\u6cbc\uff15\u9023\u6557\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u540d\uff18\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804140000565.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Howver, Shoji\u2019s return was short\u2013lived when he was sent\u2013off for a second bookable offence, in a 4\u20131 loss against Kawasaki Frontale in a follow\u2013up match.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5927\u6557\u3082\u30b5\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u6fc0\u52b1\u300c\u3082\u3046\u6211\u6162\u3057\u304b\u306a\u3044\u300d\u5185\u7530|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804210000781.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=21 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji returned from suspension, appearing in the starting line\u2013up against [[V-Varen Nagasaki]] on 2 May 2018 and helped them win 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u5f35\u672c\u4eba\u304c\u4e0b\u5411\u304b\u305a\u300d\u8ca0\u306e\u6d41\u308c\u65ad\u3063\u305f\u899a\u609f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201805020000901.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=2 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Following the World Cup, Shoji\u2019s performance during the tournament attracted interests from clubs around Europe, but he responded to the transfer speculation by stating he wanted to stay at Kashima Antlers.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u8a55\u4fa1\u6025\u4e0a\u6607\u3000\u30d5\u30e9\u30f3\u30b9\uff11\u90e8\u304c\u7372\u5f97\u8208\u5473\u3068\u5730\u5143\u7d19|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/russia2018/news/201807050000090.html |publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u306b\u3082\u6d77\u5916\u30aa\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc!\u5730\u5143\u7d19\u304c\u30d5\u30e9\u30f3\u30b91\u90e8\u30af\u30e9\u30d6\u306e\u6253\u8a3a\u3092\u5831\u9053|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248946-248946-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff16\u767a\u5927\u52dd\u3000\u6b8b\u7559\u6c7a\u3081\u305f\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u653b\u5b88\u3067\u8ca2\u732e|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807230000136.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u5de8\u984d\u30aa\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u65ad\u308a\"\u30aa\u30ec\u5c02\u7528\"\u5e2b\u5320\u3068\u62b1\u64c1|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811120000075.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 22 July 2018 when Shoji made his return to the starting line-up as captain against [[Kashiwa Reysol]] and led the side to win 6\u20132.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff16\u767a\u5927\u52dd\uff01\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\uff13\u6226\u3076\u308a\u52dd\u5229\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u67cf17\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807230000487.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, his return was short\u2013lived when he suffered ankle injury and had to be substituted in the 41st minutes during a 2\u20130 win against [[Cerezo Osaka]] on 25 July 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff12\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3001\uff23\u5927\u962a\uff37\u676f\u5f8c\u52dd\u5229\u7121\u3057\uff0f\uff23\uff0d\u9e7f14\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807250000840.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Initially out for three weeks, Shoji was eventually sidelined for three months.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u75db\u3044\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u96e2\u8131\u3001\u5de6\u8db3\u95a2\u7bc0\u637b\u632b\u3067\u5168\u6cbb\uff13\u9031\u9593|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807260000769.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u5fa9\u5e30\u307e\u3067\u300c\uff11\u30ab\u6708\u300d\u30e1\u30f3\u30bf\u30eb\u306e\u5f71\u97ff\u306f\u5426\u5b9a|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810020000057.html|publisher=Nikkan Sport|language=Japanese|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 14 October 2018 when he made his return from injury, coming on as a late substitute, in a 2\u20132 against Yokohama F. Marinos in the second leg of the J. League Cup semi\u2013finals, resulting Kashima Antlers\u2019 elimination.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u5fa9\u5e30\u3000\u3051\u304c\u306e\u5de6\u8db3\u9996\u300c\u9577\u3044\u4ed8\u304d\u5408\u3044\u306b\u306a\u308b\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810140000630.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 October 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Ten days later on 24 October 2018 against [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings]] in the second leg of the AFC Champions League semi\u2013finals, Shoji captained the side and led them to a 3\u20133 draw, resulting Kashima Antlers reaching the AFC Champions League Final for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5287\u7684\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\u60b2\u9858\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa\uff0f\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810230000838.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 October 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He then played in both legs of the [[2018 AFC Champions League Final|AFC Champions League Final]] against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] and led the side by beating them 2\u20130 aggregate to win the club\u2019s first AFC Champions League trophy.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5148\u52dd\uff01\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u738b\u8005\u3078\u524d\u9032\uff0f\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u6c7a\u52dd\u7b2c\uff11\u6226\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811020000891.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u521d\u5236\u8987\uff01\u6211\u6162\u809d\u306b\u7dcf\u529b\u6226\u3067\u793a\u3057\u305f\u4e00\u4f53\u611f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811100000910.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=11 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30015\u5e74\u9593\u306e\u6b74\u4ee3\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30e1\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30022\u51a0&\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u5236\u8987\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3082\u2026\u9060\u3056\u304b\u308b\u56fd\u5185\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u306e\u9053\n|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/03/19/post367437/4/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 24 November 2018 when Shoji scored his first goal of the season, in a 3\u20130 win against Vegalta Sendai.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3055\u3059\u304c\u5143\uff26\uff37\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u6280\u3042\u308a\u5f3e\u300c\u3046\u308f\u5165\u3063\u305f\u3093\u3084\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811240000627.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=24 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He later appeared twice during the [[2018 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]], as they finished fourth place in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=2\u5e74\u524d\u3068\u306e\u9055\u3044\u3092\u5b9f\u611f\u3059\u308b\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u30ec\u30a2\u30eb\u3068\u306e\u30ea\u30d9\u30f3\u30b8\u30de\u30c3\u30c1\u3078\u300c\u6b21\u306f\u52dd\u3061\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?261632-261632-fl|publisher=Web Gekisala|language=Japanese|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5b8c\u6557\u3000\u6d99\u306e\u5185\u7530\u300c\u3053\u306e\u7d4c\u9a13\u3092\u7121\u99c4\u306b\u3057\u3066\u306f\u2026\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201812210000016.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=21 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2018 season, Shoji went on to make thirty appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\n===Toulouse FC===\nIn November 2018, Shoji continued to be linked a move away from Kashima Antlers, as it was reported that [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] interested in signing him.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u306b\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u304c\u71b1\u8996\u7dda\u3000\u4ecf\u7d19\u304c\u5831\u9053|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201811150000154.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=15 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It was announced on 29 December 2018 that he signed for Toulouse, signing a three\u2013year contract for a transfer fee of 3 million euros and becoming the first Japanese player to join the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toulouse : accord officiel pour le Japonais Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Toulouse-accord-officiel-pour-le-japonais-gen-shoji/972722|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=29 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Cinq choses \u00e0 savoir sur Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/cinq-choses-savoir-sur-gen-shoji,47817.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=5 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Upon joining the club, Shoji said he will do his best at Toulouse and learn the speak the French language as quickly as possible.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"En France, je vais faire de mon mieux\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-en-france-je-vais-faire-de-mon-mieux-,47772.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=1 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'ai l'intention d'apprendre le fran\u00e7ais le plus rapidement possible\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-ai-l-intention-d-apprendre-le-francais-le-plus-rapidement-possible-,47836.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=6 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nShoji made his Toulouse debut, starting the whole game and keeping a clean sheet, in a 1\u20130 win against [[N\u00eemes Olympique]] on 19 January 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ligue 1 : Toulouse se fait du bien \u00e0 N\u00eemes|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Toulouse-se-fait-du-bien-a-nimes/979381|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=19 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He kept another clean sheet in a follow\u2013up match against [[Angers SCO]], as they drew 0\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ligue 1 : Toulouse et Angers dos \u00e0 dos|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ligue-1-toulouse-et-angers-dos-a-dos/982448|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=27 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Since joining the club, Shoji became a first team regular for the club, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"Je veux apporter mon esprit de comp\u00e9titeur, \u00e7a manquait un peu \u00e0 Toulouse\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-je-veux-apporter-mon-esprit-de-competiteur-ca-manquait-un-peu-a-toulouse-,48943.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=ASSE - TFC : La d\u00e9fense \u00e0 cinq sera reconduite|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/asse-tfc-la-defense-a-cinq-sera-reconduite,49235.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=28 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'ai une pr\u00e9f\u00e9rence pour un sch\u00e9ma \u00e0 deux d\u00e9fenseurs centraux, plut\u00f4t qu'\u00e0 trois\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-ai-une-preference-pour-un-schema-a-deux-defenseurs-centraux-plutot-qu-a-trois-,49382.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Manager [[Alain Casanova]] described Shoji\u2019s signings as a \"very good pick\" after watching his performance but expected him to improve.<ref>{{cite news|title=Casanova : \"Shoji, une tr\u00e8s bonne pioche de notre recrutement\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/casanova-shoji-une-tres-bonne-pioche-de-notre-recrutement-,48955.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=4 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Casanova : \"Shoji cherche \u00e0 s'am\u00e9liorer en permanence\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/casanova-shoji-cherche-a-s-ameliorer-en-permanence-,49383.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji was able to help to help the club avoid relegation despite bad results.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3082\u30bb\u30b9\u30af\u306b\uff36\u5f3e\u6d74\u3073\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u6557\u308c\u308b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201902030000032.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 February 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b5016\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3000\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u5f15\u304d\u5206\u3051|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201905120000080.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u79fb\u7c4d\u5f8c\u516818\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3000\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201905250000088.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2018\u201319 season, he made twenty appearances in all competitions.\n\nAhead of the 2019\u201320 season, however, Shoji suffered a hamstring injury during a pre\u2013season match in a 1\u20130 defeat against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] and was sidelined for a month.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brest - TFC : Gen Shoji vers un forfait|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/brest-tfc-gen-shoji-vers-un-forfait,50320.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=7 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji absent plusieurs semaines?|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-absent-plusieurs-semaines-,50414.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=14 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=PSG - TFC : Gen Shoji toujours \u00e0 l'infirmerie|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/psg-tfc-gen-shoji-toujours-a-l-infirmerie,50533.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=24 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 6 September 2019 when he made his return from injury, appearing in a friendly match against [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite news|title=TFC 1-2 Athletic Bilbao : Les 3 choses \u00e0 retenir et les notes sur 10|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/tfc-1-2-athletic-bilbao-les-3-choses-a-retenir-et-les-notes-sur-10,50722.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=6 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 25 September 2019 when Shoji made his first league appearance of the season and started the match, as Toulouse lost 2\u20130 against Angers SCO.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u5148\u767a\u3082\u8ca0\u50b7\u3067\u524d\u534a\u4ea4\u4ee3\u3000\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u306f\u6557\u308c\u308b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201909260000013.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji played 45 minutes, as he sprained his ankle and was substituted.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji victime d'une entorse|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-victime-d-une-entorse,50949.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=25 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> This turns out to be his only appearance for the club this season. Initially out for three weeks, Shoji was sidelined for months and never played for Toulouse again.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji absent plusieurs semaines|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-absent-plusieurs-semaines,50968.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=27 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji rechute, Sa\u00efd et Sangar\u00e9 incertains, le point sur l'infirmerie|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-rechute-said-et-sangare-incertains-le-point-sur-l-infirmerie,51516.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Bless\u00e9, Gen Shoji part au Japon se faire soigner|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/blesse-gen-shoji-part-au-japon-se-faire-soigner,51953.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=13 December 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It was reported in late\u2013January that Toulouse accepted a bid from Gamba Osaka for Shoji.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : Une offre venue du Japon pour Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-une-offre-venue-du-japon-pour-gen-shoji,52542.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Upon leaving the club, it was reported that Shoji wanted to leave the club, having failed to settle in France and later stated it was a difficult decision to leave.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : C'est Shoji qui a envie de partir|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-c-est-shoji-qui-a-envie-de-partir,52547.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'\u00e9tais perdu \u00e0 Toulouse, mais c'\u00e9tait une d\u00e9cision difficile de partir\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-etais-perdu-a-toulouse-mais-c-etait-une-decision-difficile-de-partir-,52717.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Toulouse. Gen Shoji, entre culpabilit\u00e9 et mal du pays|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/02/05/gen-shoji-entre-culpabilite-et-mal-du-pays,8711438.php|publisher=La Depeche|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Gamba Osaka===\nIt was announced on 3 February 2020 that [[Gamba Osaka]] signed Shoji on a five\u2013year contract for a reported transfer fee of 850,000 euros.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : La presse japonaise d\u00e9voile le prix du transfert de Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-la-presse-japonaise-devoile-le-prix-du-transfert-de-gen-shoji,52609.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/10810/|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\u9078\u624b \u30ac\u30f3\u30d0\u5927\u962a\u3078\u5b8c\u5168\u79fb\u7c4d\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|publisher=Gamba Osaka|language=Japanese|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194636/https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/10810/|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Gen Shoji.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Shoji trying to defend the ball from [[Romelu Lukaku]] during a quarter\u2013final match in the World Cup against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] on 2 July 2018.]]\n\nIt was announced on 1 October 2014 that Shoji was called up for the [[Japan national football team|Japan]]\u2019s squad for the first time by Manager [[Javier Aguirre]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u306b\u9999\u5ddd\u3089\u5fa9\u5e30!!\u5c0f\u6797\u60a0\u3001\u5869\u8c37\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u521d\u9078\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?148423-148423-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he withdrew from the squad, due to an injury.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u53f3\u592a\u3082\u3082\u88cf\u8ca0\u50b7\u3067\u4ee3\u8868\u8f9e\u9000|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/f-sc-tp2-20141005-1377979.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Two months later, it was announced that Shoji was called up for the national team ahead of the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup|AFC Asian Cup]] in [[Australia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc23\u4eba\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a!!\u6e05\u6b66\u304cW\u676f\u4ee5\u6765\u306e\u5fa9\u5e30\u3067\u30a2\u30ae\u30fc\u30ecJ\u521d\u62db\u96c6|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?153584-153584-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=15 December 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he appeared as an unused substitute throughout the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u6307\u5c0e\u3057\u3066\u3082\u3089\u3063\u305f\u3053\u3068\u5fd8\u308c\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/p-sc-tp2-20150205-1430529.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 February 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=UAE\u6226\u3078\u68ee\u91cd\u3082\u5148\u767a\u30014\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u3067\u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u306b\u5909\u66f4\u306a\u3057|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?156085-156085-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u6563\u6b69\u968a\u306e\u30c6\u30fc\u30de\u306f\u300c\u690d\u7530\u306e\u5fc3\u3092\u958b\u3053\u3046\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155827-155827-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt wasn\u2019t until on 31 March 2015 when Shoji made his Japan debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a friendly match, starting the whole game, as he helped the side beat Uzbekistan 5\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4ee3\u8868\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u306f\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u306e\u9055\u3044\u306b\u3084\u3084\u6238\u60d1\u3044\u3082\u2026 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?160005-160005-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> A year later on 3 June 2016, Shoji made another appearance for Japan, coming on as the 84th minute substitute, in a 7\u20132 win against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd2\u767a!\u9ebb\u4e5f2\u767a!\u9577\u53cb\u30a2\u30b7\u30b9\u30c8\u306b\u6d45\u91ce\u3082\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u304c7\u767a\u5927\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?190934-190934-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> In December 2017, he was called up to the national team squad for the [[2017 EAFF E-1 Football Championship|EAFF E-1 Football Championship]] as a host.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uff27\u5927\u962a\u521d\u702c\u3001\u9e7f\u5cf6\u4e09\u7aff\u3089\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\uff25\uff0d\uff11\u9078\u624b\u6a29\u4ee3\u8868|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201711290000056.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji captained Japan for the first time in his career and led the side to beat [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]] 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u6210\u9577\u3067\u304d\u305f\u300d\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\u521d\u4e3b\u5c06\u3067\u7121\u5931\u70b9\u52dd\u5229|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201712090000729.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=9 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up match against [[China national football team|China]], he scored his first Japan goal, which turns out to be a winning goal, in a 2\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\u304c\u4e2d\u56fd\u7834\u308b\u3000\u5c0f\u6797\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u4ee3\u8868\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201712120000706.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Japan lost 4\u20131 to [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in a deciding match, which resulted in the opposition team becoming champions in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u306f4\u5931\u70b9\u6557\u6226\u2026\u97d3\u56fd\u79f0\u3048\u308b\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u3001\u5148\u5236\u5f8c\u306e\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u306b\u7d0d\u5f97\u3044\u304b\u305a\u300c\u306a\u305c\u305d\u3046\u306a\u3063\u305f\u306e\u304b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?233611-233611-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> After the match, Shoji reflected on the loss, saying: \"Today, Korea was amazing. There were a lot of things we had to follow. Of course, duels and balls, but it was quick to make blocks. It was ambiguous about today. I think it was a sad game.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5b88\u5099\u5d29\u58ca\u2026\u5c48\u8fb14\u5931\u70b9\u306b\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u60c5\u3051\u306a\u3044\u8a66\u5408\u3060\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?233627-233627-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, Shoji was named in Japan's preliminary [[Japan national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u897f\u91ceJ\u59cb\u52d5\u3078\u2026W\u676f\u6700\u7d42\u5019\u88dc27\u4eba\u306b\u672c\u7530\u3001\u9999\u5ddd\u3089\u3092\u9078\u51fa!!\u9752\u5c71\u304c\u30b5\u30d7\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?245043-245043-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Eventually, he made it to the final cut of the 23 men squad.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=ja:\u9152\u4e95\u5b8f\u6a39\u30012\u5ea6\u76ee\u306eW\u676f\u306b\u610f\u6c17\u8fbc\u3080\u300c\u3053\u306e4\u5e74\u9593\u78e8\u304d\u4e0a\u3052\u305f\u3082\u306e\u3092\u2026\u300d|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2018/05/31/post272190/|publisher=Football Channel Website|language=Japanese|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u897f\u91ce\u76e3\u7763\u306e\u65b0\u6226\u8853\u300c\uff13\uff0d\uff14\uff0d\uff13\u300d\u9577\u8c37\u90e8\u304c\uff23\uff22\u306b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201805260000796.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji made his World Cup debut against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in Matchday 1 of the Group Stage, where he played the whole game, in a 2-1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=World Cup: Japan beat 10-man Colombia in Group H|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439048|publisher=BBC Sport|date=19 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji later made two more starts in the tournament, as they were eliminated by [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u521d\u51fa\u5834\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u300c10\u4eba\u306a\u306e\u304b\u3068\u601d\u3046\u3050\u3089\u3044\u306e\u5727\u529b\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/russia2018/news/201806200000204.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u72d9\u308f\u308c\u305f\u660c\u5b50!? \u300c\u3042\u3063\u3001\u4ffa\u3060\u306a\u3068\u5206\u304b\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248102-248102-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u307f\u3093\u306a\u3067\u63a1\u70b9!!8\u5f37\u306b\u6311\u3093\u3060\u30d9\u30eb\u30ae\u30fc\u6226\u3001\u6700\u3082\u8a55\u4fa1\u304c\u9ad8\u304b\u3063\u305f\u306e\u306f\u2026|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248835-248835-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shortly after, [[Fox Sports]] named Shoji in the Asian\u2019s Best Eleven of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u300c\u30b5\u30e0\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u3067\u6700\u9ad8\u306e\u30d1\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30de\u30f3\u30b9\u300d\u3001\u6d77\u5916\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304cW\u676f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u30d9\u30b9\u30c811\u3092\u9078\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?249070-249070-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the tournament, Shoji didn\u2019t receive a call up from the national team until March 2019 for a match against Colombia, which he played against and the side lost 1\u20130 on 22 March 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4ee3\u8868\u5fa9\u5e30\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u4e00\u756a\u4e57\u308a\u3067\u5e30\u56fd\u3000\u300c\u697d\u3057\u307f\u300d\u3068\u7b11\u9854|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201903170000144.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=17 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u524d\u534a\u306e\u597d\u6a5f\u751f\u304b\u305b\u305aPK\u306b\u6c88\u3080\u2026\u68ee\u4fddJ\u3001\u30b3\u30ed\u30f3\u30d3\u30a2\u306b0-1\u6557\u6226|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?269432-269432-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Three months later in June, Shoji started two more matches back to back for the national side, including being a captain against [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] on 9 June 2019 and helping them kept two clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u76f8\u624bGK\u304c\u597d\u5b88\u9023\u767a\u20263\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u521d\u63a1\u7528\u306e\u68ee\u4fddJ\u306f\u521d\u306e\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u30ec\u30b9\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?276299-276299-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 June 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u521d\u4e3b\u5c06\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u58f0\u901a\u3063\u3066\u304f\u308c\u305f\u300d\uff13\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u7d71\u7387\u3067\uff10\u5c01|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201906090001135.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=9 June 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{Updated|1 July 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway}}</ref><ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/2016J1-J2-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411335/ref=pd_cp_14_1?ie=UTF8&refRID=1N6B11BBGDQ32GYF7MWJ \"2016J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451\"], 10 February 2016, Japan, {{ISBN|978-4905411338}} (p. 42 out of 289)</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>[[#notes gs1|1]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Kashima Antlers]]\n|[[2011 J. League Division 1|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[J. League Division 1]]\n|0||0||2||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||2||0\n|-\n|[[2012 J. League Division 1|2012]]\n|9||0||4||1||5||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||18||1\n|-\n|[[2013 J. League Division 1|2013]]\n|4||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||5||0\n|-\n|[[2014 J. League Division 1|2014]]\n|34||2||0||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||40||2\n|-\n|[[2015 J1 League|2015]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[J1 League]]\n|29||3||0||0||4||0||5||0||0||0||38||3\n|-\n|[[2016 J1 League|2016]]\n|34||1||4||0||2||1||0||0||5||0||45||2\n|-\n|[[2017 J1 League|2017]]\n|34||1||2||1||1||0||8||0||1||0||46||2\n|-\n|[[2018 J1 League|2018]]\n|16||1||2||0||1||0||9||0||2||0||30||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!160||8||14||2||20||1||22||0||8||0||224||11\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Ligue 1|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[Ligue 1]]\n|18||0||2||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||20||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!178||8||16||2||20||1||22||0||8||0||244||10\n|-\n|}\n\n<div id=\"notes gs1\"></div><sup>1</sup><small>Includes [[Suruga Bank Championship]], [[FIFA World Cup]]</small>\n\n===International===\n{{updated|8 November 2019|<ref name=\"JNFTD\">[http://www.jfootball-db.com/players_sa/gen_shoji.html Japan National Football Team Database]{{in lang|ja}}</ref><ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/58971/Gen_Shoji.html|title=Sh\u014dji, Gen|publisher=National Football Teams|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Japan national football team|Japan]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[2015 Japan national football team|2015]]||1||0\n|-\n|[[2016 Japan national football team|2016]]||1||0\n|-\n|[[2017 Japan national football team|2017]]||8||1\n|-\n|[[2018 Japan national football team|2018]]||5||0\n|-\n|[[2019 Japan national football team|2019]]||3||0\n|-\n!Total||18||1\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Japan's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 12 December 2017 || [[Ajinomoto Stadium]], [[Tokyo]], Japan || {{fb|CHN}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 2\u20131 || [[2017 EAFF E-1 Football Championship]]\n|}\n\n==Personal life==\nWhen Shoji was two years old, [[Great Hanshin earthquake]] struck in his hometown. He said about the thoughts, saying: \"I listened to my father and mother and did some research on my own. You must never forget. I want to do my best on behalf of Kobe as long as I carry the country, regardless of whether I go to the match or not.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd\u3001\u5ca1\u5d0e\u3068\u3068\u3082\u306b\u2026\u795e\u6238\u51fa\u8eab\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u9707\u707d20\u5e74\u306e\u6c7a\u610f|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155818-155818-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> His father works as the chief of the technical committee chairman of the Hyogo Football Association.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uff3b\u82e5\u304d\u30b5\u30e0\u30e9\u30a4 \u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff031 \uff3dDF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c1\u5bfe1\u3067\u306f\u8ab0\u306b\u3082\u8ca0\u3051\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://www.theworldmagazine.jp/20150628/05feature/8814|publisher=The World Magazine|language=Japanese|date=28 June 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u30d0\u30f3\u30c7\u30a3\u30aa\u30f3\u30bb\u52a0\u53e4\u5ddd\u3000\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u7d4c\u55b6\u53c2\u52a0\u3092\u6b63\u5f0f\u767a\u8868|url=https://www.kobe-np.co.jp/news/sports/201909/0012663152.shtml|publisher=Kobe Shimbun|language=Japanese|date=2 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji has an older sister, Kaede Masako, who is an actress.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30fb\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u59c9\u3001\u6953\u304c\u559c\u3073\u306e\u624b\u8a18\uff01\uff37\u676f\"\u71c3\u3048\u5c3d\u304d\u75c7\u5019\u7fa4\"\u4e57\u308a\u8d8a\u3048\u305f\u300c\u6e90\u3001\u304a\u3081\u3067\u3068\u3046\u300d|url=https://www.sanspo.com/soccer/news/20181112/jle18111210000002-n1.html|publisher=Sanspo|language=Japanese|date=12 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Shoji announced his marriage to a general woman, which took place in the previous October.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u304c\u7d50\u5a5a\u767a\u8868\u3000\u6628\u5e7410\u6708\u306b\u4e00\u822c\u5973\u6027\u3068|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1761181.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 January 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Outside of football, he said he watches movies, stating it has helped him relive stress.<ref>{{cite news|title=J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3055\u3093\u306b\u805e\u304f10\u306e\u3053\u3068|url=https://style.nikkei.com/article/DGXMZO12619080X00C17A2UP1000?channel=DF220420167274|publisher=Nikkei Style|language=Japanese|date=10 February 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n*[[J. League Division 1]]: [[2016 J1 League|2016]]\n*[[AFC Champions League]]: [[2018 AFC Champions League|2018]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[J. League Best Eleven]]: [[2016 J1 League|2016]], [[2017 J1 League|2017]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{FIFA player|384847}}\n*{{NFT}}\n*{{J.League player}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140104053609/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/clubs/3.html Profile at Kashima Antlers]\n\n{{Gamba Osaka squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{2016 J.League Team of the Year}}\n{{2017 J.League Team of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title= Japan squads\n|bg= mediumblue\n|fg= white\n|bordercolor= red\n|list1=\n{{Japan squad 2015 AFC Asian Cup}}\n{{Japan squad 2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shoji, Gen}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football people from Hy\u014dgo Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Kobe]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japan international footballers]]\n[[Category:J1 League players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Kashima Antlers players]]\n[[Category:Toulouse FC players]]\n[[Category:2015 AFC Asian Cup players]]\n[[Category:2018 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Gen Sh\u014dji\n| image = Gen Shoji (cropped).jpg\n| caption = Shoji with [[Japan national football team|Japan]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname = Gen Sh\u014dji\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|12|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Kobe]], Japan\n| height = 1.82 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |date=4 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Gamba Osaka]]\n| clubnumber = 3\n| youthyears1 = 2008\u20132010\n| youthclubs1 = Yonago Kita High School\n| years1 = 2011\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[Kashima Antlers]]\n| caps1 = 160\n| goals1 = 8\n| years2 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs2 = [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]]\n| caps2 = 19\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[Gamba Osaka]]\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Japan national football team|Japan]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 18\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n|medaltemplates=\n{{Medal|Team|[[Kashima Antlers]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[AFC Champions League]]|[[2018 AFC Champions League|2018]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[J1 League]]|[[2016 J1 League|2016]]}}\n{{Medal|RU|[[J1 League]]|[[2017 J1 League|2017]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[J.League Cup]]|[[2011 J.League Cup|2011]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[J.League Cup]]|[[2012 J.League Cup|2012]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[J.League Cup]]|[[2015 J.League Cup|2015]]}}\n{{Medal|W|[[Emperor's Cup]]|[[2016 Emperor's Cup|2016]]}}\n| club-update = 3 February 2020\n| ntupdate = 18:50, 8 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Gen Sh\u014dji'''|\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90|''Sh\u014dji Gen''|born 11 December 1992}} is a Japanese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Gamba Osaka]] in the Japanese [[J1 League]].\n\nA strong and physical centre\u2013back defender, Shoji is capable of covering and positioning using speed, as well as, his increase strength and intensity of one on one.<ref name=\"Shoji2\">{{cite web|url=https://news.biglobe.ne.jp/sports/1105/fot_151105_2180420237.html|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u6b21\u4e16\u4ee3\u62c5\u3046\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3002\"\u5e38\u52dd\u8ecd\u56e3\"\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u3001\u82e5\u304dDF\u30ea\u30fc\u30c0\u30fc\u304c\u80cc\u8ca0\u3046\u4f7f\u547d\u611f\u3068\u899a\u609f|publisher=Big Globe|language=Japanese|date=5 November 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407154029/https://news.biglobe.ne.jp/sports/1105/fot_151105_2180420237.html|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji3\">{{cite web|url=https://qoly.jp/player/worldchampionship/profile/700-762-2174-17503|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90|publisher=Qoly Football|language=Japanese|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150129031826/https://qoly.jp/player/worldchampionship/profile/700-762-2174-17503|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=[Y\u2606voice_36]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u30d8\u30c7\u30a3\u30f3\u30b0\u306f\u8ab0\u306b\u3082\u8ca0\u3051\u305f\u304f\u306a\u3044\u3001\u81ea\u4fe1\u304c\u3042\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?72916-61806-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 August 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u304c\u540dDF\u3092\u8f29\u51fa\u3057\u7d9a\u3051\u308b\u7406\u7531--\u79cb\u7530\u8c4a\u00d7\u4e2d\u7530\u6d69\u30cb\u00d7\u660c\u5b50\u6e90|url=https://logmi.jp/business/articles/40520|publisher=Logmi Biz|language=Japanese|date=19 February 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Kashima Antlers===\nBorn in [[Kobe]], Japan, Sh\u014dji started playing football when he was two years old, starting out in a forward position.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\"/> His performance when he was in fourth grade playing against the sixth grade attracted attention from Fresca Kobe U12 (Hyogo Prefecture), who signed him.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/clubs/shoji-gen.html|title=\u80cc\u756a\u53f73\u306e\u91cd\u307f\u3002\u6311\u6226\u306f\u7d9a\u304f\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161219035637/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/clubs/shoji-gen.html|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He joined Gamba Osaka Junior Youth during middle school and then Yonago Kita High School.<ref name=\"Sh\u014dji 1\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=[j\u9ad8\u6821\u7dcf\u4f53]\u4f50\u8cc0\u6771vs\u7c73\u5b50\u5317 \u8a66\u5408\u8a18\u9332|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?57829-40488-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=7 August 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u9ad8\u6821\u7dcf\u4f53]\u5927\u4f1a\u512a\u79c0\u9078\u624b\u306b\u897f\u6fa4\u3001\u8c37\u5c3e\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u3001\u98a8\u9593\u5144\u3089|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?57893-40586-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=8 August 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u5168\u65e5\u672c\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9(U-18)\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u5f37\u529b\u3060\u3063\u305f\"\u30dc\u30fc\u30eb\u72e9\u308a\"\u30682\u30c8\u30c3\u30d7\u3001\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u304c\u9759\u5b66\u6c88\u3081\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59054-42201-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[\u5168\u65e5\u672c\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9(U-18)\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u3001\u9ad8\u901f\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u3067\u5343\u8449U-18\u7c89\u7815|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59639-43037-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> While at Yonago Kita High School, Shoji switched to playing in the centre\u2013back position, a position he played today.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u9ad8\u6821MOM_62]\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u9ad8DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90(2\u5e74)_\u5148\u767a\u596a\u53d6\u534a\u5e74\u306eCB\u304c\u8105\u5a01\u306b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?59055-42202-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 September 2009|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u300cY\u2606voice_13\u300d\u7c73\u5b50\u5317DF\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u30e6\u30fc\u30b9\u3082\u610f\u8b58\u3057\u3066\u3044\u304f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?69327-56668-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=27 May 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56386?static=true|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\uff5e\u7a81\u7136\u8a00\u308f\u308c\u305f\u3001\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u3078\u306e\u8ee2\u5411\uff5e|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=24 December 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322212819/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56386?static=true|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u306e\u300c\u4f1d\u8aac\u300d\u3002\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u6311\u3080CB\u3078\u3001\u5f8c\u8f29\u305f\u3061\u304c\u30a8\u30fc\u30eb\u300c\u660c\u5b50\u9078\u624b\u306a\u3089\u7d76\u5bfe\u306b\u6b62\u3081\u3066\u304f\u308c\u308b\u306f\u305a\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?247467-247467-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At first, Shoji was unhappy with the team\u2019s decision to switch him into the centre\u2013back position, but over time, he accepted playing in the position.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56387?static=true|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\uff5e\u4e00\u5bfe\u4e00\u306f\u7d76\u5bfe\u306b\u8ca0\u3051\u306a\u3044\uff5e|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 December 2015|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322212833/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/news/member_contents/56387?static=true|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50&\u5869\u8c37\u304c\u300eNIKEiD\u300f\u3067\u611b\u7528\u30b9\u30d1\u30a4\u30af\u3092\u81ea\u5206\u597d\u307f\u306b\u30c7\u30b6\u30a4\u30f3|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?186890-186890-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 April 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced on 30 September 2010 that Shoji would be joining [[Kashima Antlers]] from 1 January 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/8865|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u9078\u624b\u306e2011\u5e74\u52a0\u5165\u5185\u5b9a\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=30 September 2010|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321230600/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/8865|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Ahead of the 2011 season, Shoji was registered to the Kashima Antlers\u2019 first team in January.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/9734|title=2011\u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f3\u306e\u767b\u9332\u9078\u624b\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=1 February 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321230638/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/release/9734|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He spoke about his expectations at his new club, saying: \"In 2011 , I want to work hard without losing, so that the directors and supporters can recognize me. I want to try out what I can do. I want to do my best to help my team.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=[\u9078\u624b\u6a29]\u67f4\u5d0e\u3089J\u52a0\u5165\u5185\u5b9a\u9078\u624b\u300c2011\u5e74\u65b0\u5e74\u306e\u8a93\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?78653-70275-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 January 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7c73\u5b50\u5317\u30fb\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u6b63\u5f0f\u5951\u7d04\u3002\u300c\u81ea\u5206\u304c\u3069\u3053\u307e\u3067\u3067\u304d\u308b\u304b\u8a66\u3057\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?79570-71503-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=21 January 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> He first appeared in the first team for Kashima Antlers as an unused substitute, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings]] in the AFC Champions League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/521|title=AFC\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30d4\u30aa\u30f3\u30ba\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c3|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 April 2013|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321231251/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/521|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> From that moment on, Shoji spent months on the substitute bench, due to [[Daiki Iwamasa]], [[Takeshi Aoki]] and [[Masahiko Inoha]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5ca9\u653f&\u4f0a\u91ce\u6ce2\u306e\u4ee3\u8868CB\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u306b\u6311\u3080\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u300cFK\u3082\u72d9\u3044\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?80162-72315-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 February 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u9023\u6226\u898b\u636e\u3048\u3066\u4e3b\u529b\u6e29\u5b58\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u3082\u521d\u306e\u30d9\u30f3\u30c1\u5165\u308a\u3078|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?83638-77471-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u4eca\u590f\u306eDF\u88dc\u5f37\u306f\u884c\u308f\u305a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?87139-81977-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=9 July 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 12 October 2011 when he made his Kashima Antlers debut, starting the whole game, in a 2\u20130 win against [[University of Tsukuba]] in the second round of the J. League Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/668|title=\u7530\u4ee3\u3001\u5927\u8feb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u7b51\u6ce2\u5927\u3092\u6483\u7834\u3002\u9806\u5f53\u306a3\u56de\u6226\u9032\u51fa\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=12 October 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321231400/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/668|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A month later on 16 November 2011 against [[Kataller Toyama]], Shoji made another appearance for the side, playing 62 minutes, in a 2\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/669|title=\u307e\u305f\u3057\u3066\u3082120\u5206\u9593\u306e\u6226\u3044\u3002\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5ef6\u9577\u6226\u3092\u5236\u30574\u56de\u6226\u9032\u51fa|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=15 November 2011|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321232140/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/669|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> At the end of the 2011 season, Shoji made two appearances for the side.\n\nIn the 2012 season, Shoji continued to remain on the substitute bench, as Iwamasa and Aoki were the first choice centre\u2013backs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/953|title=\u5f8c\u534a3\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u521d\u52dd\u5229\uff01\u3053\u308c\u3067\u30ab\u30b7\u30de\u901a\u7b97200\u52dd\u9054\u6210\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=21 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151539/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/953|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/958|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc! 7-0\u3068\u672d\u5e4c\u306b\u5927\u52dd!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=19 May 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322150808/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/958|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50143|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u30c9\u30a5\u30c8\u30e9\u3001\u5927\u8feb\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u57f7\u5ff5\u306e\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc! 2\u5e74\u9023\u7d9a\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=13 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322143931/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50143|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 24 March 2012 when he made his first appearance of the season, coming on as a 76th minutes substitute, in a 2\u20130 loss against [[Sanfrecce Hiroshima]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/949|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u958b\u5e553\u6226\u3067\u7121\u5f97\u70b9\u3001\u3044\u307e\u3060\u52dd\u5229\u306a\u3057\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=24 March 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151357/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/949|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A month later, Shoji made his first start of the season, playing in the centre\u2013back position, as he helped Kashima Antlers beat [[Hokkaido Consadole Sapporo]] in the J.League Group Stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c10\u4eba\u306e\u672d\u5e4c\u306b\u7d42\u4e86\u9593\u969b\u306e\u5287\u5f3e\u3067\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?98151-98525-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> Over the season, Shoji then played in different positions, such as, defensive midfield, left\u2013back and right\u2013back, but most of them were substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/950|title=\u307e\u305f\u3082\u30ce\u30fc\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u306a\u304c\u3089\u3001\u52dd\u70b91\u3002\u524d\u9014\u306b\u304b\u3059\u304b\u306a\u5e0c\u671b\u306e\u5149\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151357/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/950|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/952|title=\u9060\u85e4\u306e\u5287\u7684\u6c7a\u52dd\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c2-1\u3068\u4eca\u5b63\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u521d\u52dd\u5229\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=14 April 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322151359/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/952|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/986|title=\u5927\u8feb\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u3001\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229!! \u524d\u56de\u8987\u8005\u306e\u610f\u5730\u3092\u898b\u305b\u308b\u3002|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 June 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322150755/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/986|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/974|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5727\u5dfb\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc! \u30c9\u30a5\u30c8\u30e9\u306e\u521d\u30cf\u30c3\u30c8\u30c8\u30ea\u30c3\u30af\u3001\u67f4\u5d0e\u306e\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067FC\u6771\u4eac\u306b5-1\u306e\u5727\u52dd!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322143939/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/974|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 8 September 2012 when he scored his first Kashima Antlers\u2019 goal, in a 7\u20131 win against [[University of Tsukuba]] in the second round of the Emperor\u2019s Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50135|title=\u9060\u85e4\u306e3\u767a\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u516c\u5f0f\u6226\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u306a\u3069\u30677-1\u3068\u7b51\u6ce2\u5927\u3092\u6483\u7834!! |publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=8 September 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121558/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50135|archivedate=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Two months later on 3 November 2012, Shoji started in the left\u2013back position for the [[2012 J.League Cup Final|J.League Cup Final]] against [[Shimizu S-Pulse]] and played 83 minutes before being substituted, as Kashima Antlers won 2\u20131, his first title of his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50152|title=J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u6c7a\u52dd\u30c8\u30fc\u30ca\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8 \u6c7a\u52dd|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2012|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121551/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50152|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/freaksplus/20150715/todays-player.html|title=\u4eca\u65e5\u306e\u6ce8\u76ee\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u30e4\u30fc\u306f\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\uff01|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=15 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172833/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/freaksplus/20150715/todays-player.html|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After the match, Manager [[Jorginho (footballer, born 1964)|Jorginho]] evaluated his performance.<ref>{{cite news|title=19\u6b73\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u5927\u524d\u3092\u5fb9\u5e95\u30de\u30fc\u30af\u3001\u6307\u63ee\u5b98\u306e\u6307\u793a\u306f\u300c\u540c\u3058\u6c34\u3092\u98f2\u3093\u3067\u3082\u3044\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?106972-109304-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2012|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2012 season, he went on to make eighteen appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2013 season, Shoji made his first appearance of the season, coming on as a 77th minutes substitute, in a 3\u20132 win against [[Vegalta Sendai]] on 9 March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50171|title=2013\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c2\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=9 March 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820121858/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50171|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, his first team opportunities was limited, due to competitions from Iwamasa, Aoki and new signing, [[Takanori Maeno]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5ca9\u653f\u51fa\u5834\u505c\u6b62\u3067\u5c71\u6751\u3089\u82e5\u624b\u306b\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30b9|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/p-sc-tp1-20130426-1117831.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 April 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9ce5\u6816vs\u9e7f\u5cf6 \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?111381-114602-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 March 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6vs\u9ce5\u6816 \u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u767a\u8868|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?112788-116328-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 April 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Despite this, Shoji made his first league start, starting the whole game, in a 3\u20132 win against [[FC Tokyo]] on 25 May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/games/50285/match_review|title= 2013\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c13\u7bc0 FC\u6771\u4eac\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=25 May 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323212153/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/games/50285/match_review|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By June, he suffered a meniscus damage while training and was sidelined for four months, eventually ruling him out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3011\u660c\u5b50\u306f\u534a\u6708\u677f\u640d\u50b7\u3000\u5168\u6cbb\u7d04\uff14\u30ab\u6708|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/f-sc-tp1-20130620-1145208.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2013|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji3\"/> Despite this, Shoji went on to make five appearances for the side at the end of the 2013 season.\n\nIn the 2014 season, Shoji returned to the starting line-up against [[Ventforet Kofu]] in the opening game of the season and scored from a header, in a 4\u20130 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51436/live|title= 2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c1\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=1 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140310131618/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51436/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> This was followed up by helping the side keep two clean sheets in the next two matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50690|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c2\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=8 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125718/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50690|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51068/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c3\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=14 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323214958/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51068/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> His contribution to the first team helped the side finished at the top of the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51082/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c5\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 March 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323215337/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51082/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51124|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c9\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=26 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125738/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51124|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51129|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c10\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820125740/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51129|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, as the season progressed, the club\u2019s place at the top of the table soon slipped.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51161|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c14\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=17 May 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221011/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51161|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50940|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c30\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=26 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323222148/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50940|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51341|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c34\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 December 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323222145/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51341|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By September, Shoji scored his second goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Omiya Ardija]] on 13 September 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50876|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c23\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=13 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221550/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50876|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> This was followed by keeping three clean sheets in the next three matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50885|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c24\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=20 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221601/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50885|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/45299|title=J1 \u7b2c25\u7bc0 \u30d9\u30ac\u30eb\u30bf\u4ed9\u53f0\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=23 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221555/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/45299|archivedate= 28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50907/live|title=2014\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0 \u30c7\u30a3\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\uff11 \u7b2c26\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=27 September 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323221552/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/50907/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> The 2014 season proved to be Shoji\u2019s breakthrough to the Kashima Anthlers\u2019 first team, and cemented his place in the centre\u2013back position.<ref name=\"Shoji3\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u30d5\u30a9\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u5bfe\u7b56\u300c\u3055\u3055\u3084\u304d\u6226\u8853\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/p-sc-tp1-20140323-1274163.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 April 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30012014\u88dc\u5f37\u8a3a\u65ad\u3002\u6226\u529b\u4e0a\u7a4d\u307f\u306a\u304f\u3001\u540d\u9580\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u5927\u304d\u306a\u4e0d\u5b89|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2014/02/15/post26423/3/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=15 February 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the season, he went on to make forty appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2015 season, Shoji made his AFC Champions League debut, starting the whole game, as Kashima Anthlers lost 1\u20130 against [[Western Sydney Wanderers FC|Western Sydney Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a6\u30a7\u30b9\u30bf\u30f3\u30b7\u30c9\u30cb\u30fc\u3001ACL\u521d\u6226\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3092\u4e0b\u3059\uff08\u9ad8\u8429\u306e\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u52d5\u753b\u3042\u308a\uff09|url=https://qoly.jp/2015/02/25/acl-gl1-kashima-wsw|publisher=Qoly Football|language=Japanese|date=25 February 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he fractured his hand and was sidelined for weeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u5de6\u624b\u9aa8\u6298\u306e\u624b\u8853|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/1443939.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=8 March 2015|date=8 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 22 March 2015 when Shoji returned to the starting line-up, starting the whole game, in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Nagoya Grampus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/48093|title=J1 1st \u7b2c3\u7bc0 vs \u540d\u53e4\u5c4b|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=22 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323224256/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/news/match_review/48093|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> Since returning to the first team, he continued to regain his first team place for the side.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4eca\u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f3\u521d\u5b8c\u5c01\u306e\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u3053\u306e\u30bc\u30ed\u3092\u6a5f\u306b\u3001\u4f55\u304b\u304c\u5909\u308f\u3063\u305f\u3068\u601d\u3046\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?162786-162786-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=10 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051\u3092\u6094\u3084\u3080\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u3082\u3063\u3068\u3082\u3063\u3068\u5411\u4e0a\u3067\u304d\u308b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?163647-163647-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= 3\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u306e\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c2\u4f4d\u3082\u6700\u4e0b\u4f4d\u3082\u4e00\u7dd2\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?175181-175181-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306e\u6b21\u4e16\u4ee3\u62c5\u3046\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u3002\"\u5e38\u52dd\u8ecd\u56e3\"\u5fa9\u6d3b\u3078\u3001\u82e5\u304dDF\u30ea\u30fc\u30c0\u30fc\u304c\u80cc\u8ca0\u3046\u4f7f\u547d\u611f\u3068\u899a\u609f|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2015/11/05/post118219/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=5 November 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30015\u5e74\u9593\u306e\u6b74\u4ee3\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30e1\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30022\u51a0&\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u5236\u8987\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3082\u2026\u9060\u3056\u304b\u308b\u56fd\u5185\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u306e\u9053|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/03/19/post367437/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Shoji2\"/> It wasn\u2019t until on 29 April 2015 when Shoji scored his first goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against Vegalta Sendai.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51559|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c8\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=29 April 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151030022816/http://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51559|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By mid\u2013May, he began to play in the left\u2013back position from May to June.<ref name=\"Shoji4\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51575/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c13\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=23 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324171450/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51575/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51577/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c14\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=30 May 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172759/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51577/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51581/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c16\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324172828/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51581/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 11 July 2015 when Shoji scored his second goal of the season, in a 3\u20132 win against [[Albirex Niigata]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5f8c\u534aAT\u306e\u30c9\u30e9\u30de!!94\u5206\u304b\u3089\u306e2\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u65b0\u6f5f\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u3061|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?166974-166974-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Two weeks later on 25 July 2015, he scored his third goal of the season, in a 2\u20131 win against [[FC Tokyo]]<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5fa9\u5e30\u306e\u67f4\u5d0e\u304c1G1A\u3067\u5b58\u5728\u611f\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u77f3\u4e95\u4f53\u5236\u521d\u9663\u3092\u767d\u661f\u3067\u98fe\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?167972-167972-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 July 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji  suffered an injury in the 20th minutes and had to be substitute during a 2\u20132 draw against FC Tokyo in the quarter\u2013finals of the J. League Cup first leg.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6cb3\u91ce\u3001\u4e2d\u5cf6\u304c\u30a2\u30d9\u30c3\u30af\u5f3e\u3082\u2026F\u6771\u4eac\u306f\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u5206\u3051\u308b|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?171041-171041-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 September 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 26 September 2015 when he made his return from injury, starting the whole match, in a 2\u20131 loss against [[Urawa Red Diamonds]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u66fd\u30f6\u7aef\u304c\u307e\u3055\u304b\u306e\u30dd\u30ed\u30ea\u2026\u6d66\u548c\u3001\u8208\u68a0\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u5f3e\u3067\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306b\u9006\u8ee2\u52dd\u5229!!|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?172777-172777-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=26 September 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> A month later, Shoji played in both legs against [[Vissel Kobe]] in the semi\u2013finals of the J.League Cup and helped the side reach the final after winning 6\u20132 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51699/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u6c7a\u52dd\u30c8\u30fc\u30ca\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8 \u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd \u7b2c1\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=7 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324175036/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51699/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite news|title=\"\u30d2\u30ac\u30b7\u306e\u30af\u30ea\u30ed\u30ca\"\u306e\u73fe\u5728\u5730\u2026\u795e\u6238MF\u5897\u5c71\u300c\u30c9\u30ea\u30d6\u30eb\u306f\u7c21\u5358\u306b\u306f\u6b62\u3081\u3089\u308c\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?173945-173945-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=11 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> In the [[2015 J.League Cup Final|J.League Cup]] against Gamba Osaka, he started the match and helped the side with a clean sheet by beating them 3\u20130 to win the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30d1\u30c8\u30ea\u30c3\u30af\u3092\u5c01\u3058\u305f\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u30ed\u30c3\u30ab\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30e0\u304b\u3089\u6d41\u308c\u304c\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?175273-175273-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=30 October 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Following the tournament, Shoji helped the side kept two more clean sheets in the last two remaining league matches of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51631|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff15\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff12nd\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c16\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=7 November 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324175931/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51631|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306f\u52dd\u5229\u3082\u7b2c2S\u512a\u52dd\u306a\u3089\u305a\u2026\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u3082\u897f\u91ce\u76e3\u7763\u306e\u6700\u7d42\u6226\u3092\u767d\u661f\u3067\u98fe\u308c\u305a|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?176969-176969-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 November 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2015 season, he went on to make thirty\u2013eight appearances and scoring three times in all competitions.\n\nIn the 2016 season, Shoji started the season when he helped Kashima Antlers kept two clean sheets in the first two league matches of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=G\u5927\u962a\u3001\u65b0\u30b9\u30bf\u516c\u5f0f\u6226\u521d\u6226\u306f\u9ed2\u661f\u2026\u4ea4\u4ee3\u7b56\u7684\u4e2d\u306e\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u767d\u661f\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20160228/405992.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=Japanese|date=28 February 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/sp/games/51727/match_review|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c2\u7bc0 \u30b5\u30ac\u30f3\u9ce5\u6816\u6226|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=5 March 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Since the start of the season, Shoji continued to regain his first team place, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u67cf \u5947\u8de1\u7684V\u5b57\u56de\u5fa9\u30012\u4f4d\u9e7f\u5cf6\u6483\u7834\u3067\u516c\u5f0f\u62265\u9023\u52dd!!\u300c\u3053\u306e\u307e\u307e\u52dd\u3061\u7d9a\u3051\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?188047-188047-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=24 April 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51834/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c5\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=18 May 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325193845/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51834/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51786|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c13\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=21 May 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325193843/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51786|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 6 April 2016 when he scored his first goal of the season, in a 3\u20131 win against Nagoya Grampus in the J.League Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51831/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\uff2a\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u30e4\u30de\u30b6\u30ad\u30ca\u30d3\u30b9\u30b3\u30ab\u30c3\u30d7 \u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c3\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=6 April 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325192847/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51831/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> By the end of the J.League first stage, Shoji\u2019s contribution to the first team helped the side finished at the top of the table.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51787/live|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c15\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=11 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325193821/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51787/live|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51788|title=\uff12\uff10\uff11\uff16\u660e\u6cbb\u5b89\u7530\u751f\u547d\uff2a\uff11\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u3000\uff11\uff53\uff54\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b8 \u7b2c16\u7bc0|publisher=Kashima Antlers|language=Japanese|date=18 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325193815/https://www.so-net.ne.jp/antlers/games/51788|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> After serving a one match suspension, he made his return to the starting line-up, as Kashima Antlers lost 3\u20131 loss against Gamba Osaka on 2 July 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\u7b2c1S\u5236\u8987!! \u5c71\u672c&\u571f\u5c45\u5f3e\u30676\u9023\u52dd\u30d5\u30a3\u30cb\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?192555-192555-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u7b2c1S\u8987\u8005\u304c\u521d\u306e3\u5931\u70b9\u3067\u9ed2\u661f\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6DF\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u7518\u3055\u304c\u7d50\u679c\u306b\u51fa\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?193134-193134-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=2 July 2016|accessdate=