802250000665.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 February 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u91d1\u5d0e\uff36\u5f3e\u3001\u653b\u5b88\u306b\u5b58\u5728\u611f\u306e\u5c0f\u7b20\u539f\u306b\u300c\u5168\u7136\u9055\u3046\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201803030000783.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He then captained the side for the next three matches between on 13 March 2018 and 31 March 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30d7\u30ed\u521d\u5148\u767a\u306e19\u6b73\u5c0f\u7530\u304c\u5148\u5236\u70b9\u6f14\u51fa\u3082\u2026\u9e7f\u5cf6\u306f\u30db\u30fc\u30e0\u3067\u8ffd\u3044\u3064\u304b\u308c\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?239649-239649-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=13 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\uff2a\uff11\u9ce5\u6816\u3001\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5727\u5012\u3057\u305f\u306e\u306b\u2026\u521d\u9ed2\u661f\u3000\u30d5\u30a3\u30c3\u30ab\u30c7\u30f3\u30c6\u30a3\u76e3\u7763\u306f\u624b\u5fdc\u3048|url=https://www.nishinippon.co.jp/nsp/item/n/402132/|publisher=Nishi Nippon|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u672d\u5e4c\u3068\u3082\u306b\u597d\u6a5f\u751f\u304b\u305b\u305a\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u672d\uff15\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201803310001094.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji suffered a calf injury that saw him missed two matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u76e3\u7763\u300c\u3084\u308b\u3079\u304d\u3053\u3068\u3084\u3063\u3066\u304f\u308c\u305f\u300d\u9078\u624b\u306b\u611f\u8b1d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804040000005.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=4 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 14 April 2018 when he made his return to the starting line-up from injury, in a 2\u20130 win against Nagoya Grampus.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u91d1\u5d0e\uff12\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3001\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u306f\u6ce5\u6cbc\uff15\u9023\u6557\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u540d\uff18\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804140000565.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Howver, Shoji\u2019s return was short\u2013lived when he was sent\u2013off for a second bookable offence, in a 4\u20131 loss against Kawasaki Frontale in a follow\u2013up match.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5927\u6557\u3082\u30b5\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u6fc0\u52b1\u300c\u3082\u3046\u6211\u6162\u3057\u304b\u306a\u3044\u300d\u5185\u7530|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201804210000781.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=21 April 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji returned from suspension, appearing in the starting line\u2013up against [[V-Varen Nagasaki]] on 2 May 2018 and helped them win 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u5f35\u672c\u4eba\u304c\u4e0b\u5411\u304b\u305a\u300d\u8ca0\u306e\u6d41\u308c\u65ad\u3063\u305f\u899a\u609f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201805020000901.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=2 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Following the World Cup, Shoji\u2019s performance during the tournament attracted interests from clubs around Europe, but he responded to the transfer speculation by stating he wanted to stay at Kashima Antlers.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u306e\u8a55\u4fa1\u6025\u4e0a\u6607\u3000\u30d5\u30e9\u30f3\u30b9\uff11\u90e8\u304c\u7372\u5f97\u8208\u5473\u3068\u5730\u5143\u7d19|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/russia2018/news/201807050000090.html |publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u306b\u3082\u6d77\u5916\u30aa\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc!\u5730\u5143\u7d19\u304c\u30d5\u30e9\u30f3\u30b91\u90e8\u30af\u30e9\u30d6\u306e\u6253\u8a3a\u3092\u5831\u9053|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248946-248946-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=4 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff16\u767a\u5927\u52dd\u3000\u6b8b\u7559\u6c7a\u3081\u305f\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u653b\u5b88\u3067\u8ca2\u732e|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807230000136.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u5de8\u984d\u30aa\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u65ad\u308a\"\u30aa\u30ec\u5c02\u7528\"\u5e2b\u5320\u3068\u62b1\u64c1|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811120000075.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 22 July 2018 when Shoji made his return to the starting line-up as captain against [[Kashiwa Reysol]] and led the side to win 6\u20132.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff16\u767a\u5927\u52dd\uff01\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u6226\uff13\u6226\u3076\u308a\u52dd\u5229\uff0f\u9e7f\uff0d\u67cf17\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807230000487.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, his return was short\u2013lived when he suffered ankle injury and had to be substituted in the 41st minutes during a 2\u20130 win against [[Cerezo Osaka]] on 25 July 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\uff12\u767a\u5feb\u52dd\u3001\uff23\u5927\u962a\uff37\u676f\u5f8c\u52dd\u5229\u7121\u3057\uff0f\uff23\uff0d\u9e7f14\u7bc0|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807250000840.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Initially out for three weeks, Shoji was eventually sidelined for three months.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u75db\u3044\uff24\uff26\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u96e2\u8131\u3001\u5de6\u8db3\u95a2\u7bc0\u637b\u632b\u3067\u5168\u6cbb\uff13\u9031\u9593|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201807260000769.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u5fa9\u5e30\u307e\u3067\u300c\uff11\u30ab\u6708\u300d\u30e1\u30f3\u30bf\u30eb\u306e\u5f71\u97ff\u306f\u5426\u5b9a|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810020000057.html|publisher=Nikkan Sport|language=Japanese|date=2 October 2018}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 14 October 2018 when he made his return from injury, coming on as a late substitute, in a 2\u20132 against Yokohama F. Marinos in the second leg of the J. League Cup semi\u2013finals, resulting Kashima Antlers\u2019 elimination.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u5fa9\u5e30\u3000\u3051\u304c\u306e\u5de6\u8db3\u9996\u300c\u9577\u3044\u4ed8\u304d\u5408\u3044\u306b\u306a\u308b\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810140000630.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=14 October 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Ten days later on 24 October 2018 against [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings]] in the second leg of the AFC Champions League semi\u2013finals, Shoji captained the side and led them to a 3\u20133 draw, resulting Kashima Antlers reaching the AFC Champions League Final for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3001\u5287\u7684\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc\u60b2\u9858\u306e\u6c7a\u52dd\u9032\u51fa\uff0f\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u6e96\u6c7a\u52dd\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201810230000838.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=23 October 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He then played in both legs of the [[2018 AFC Champions League Final|AFC Champions League Final]] against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] and led the side by beating them 2\u20130 aggregate to win the club\u2019s first AFC Champions League trophy.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5148\u52dd\uff01\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u738b\u8005\u3078\u524d\u9032\uff0f\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u6c7a\u52dd\u7b2c\uff11\u6226\u8a73\u7d30|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811020000891.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u304c\uff21\uff23\uff2c\u521d\u5236\u8987\uff01\u6211\u6162\u809d\u306b\u7dcf\u529b\u6226\u3067\u793a\u3057\u305f\u4e00\u4f53\u611f|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811100000910.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=11 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u30a2\u30f3\u30c8\u30e9\u30fc\u30ba\u30015\u5e74\u9593\u306e\u6b74\u4ee3\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30e1\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u30022\u51a0&\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u5236\u8987\u3092\u7d4c\u9a13\u3082\u2026\u9060\u3056\u304b\u308b\u56fd\u5185\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u3078\u306e\u9053\n|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/03/19/post367437/4/|publisher=Football Channel|language=Japanese|date=19 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 24 November 2018 when Shoji scored his first goal of the season, in a 3\u20130 win against Vegalta Sendai.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3055\u3059\u304c\u5143\uff26\uff37\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u6280\u3042\u308a\u5f3e\u300c\u3046\u308f\u5165\u3063\u305f\u3093\u3084\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201811240000627.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=24 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He later appeared twice during the [[2018 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]], as they finished fourth place in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=2\u5e74\u524d\u3068\u306e\u9055\u3044\u3092\u5b9f\u611f\u3059\u308b\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u30ec\u30a2\u30eb\u3068\u306e\u30ea\u30d9\u30f3\u30b8\u30de\u30c3\u30c1\u3078\u300c\u6b21\u306f\u52dd\u3061\u305f\u3044\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?261632-261632-fl|publisher=Web Gekisala|language=Japanese|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u5b8c\u6557\u3000\u6d99\u306e\u5185\u7530\u300c\u3053\u306e\u7d4c\u9a13\u3092\u7121\u99c4\u306b\u3057\u3066\u306f\u2026\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/201812210000016.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=21 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2018 season, Shoji went on to make thirty appearances and scoring once in all competitions.\n\n===Toulouse FC===\nIn November 2018, Shoji continued to be linked a move away from Kashima Antlers, as it was reported that [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] interested in signing him.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u306b\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u304c\u71b1\u8996\u7dda\u3000\u4ecf\u7d19\u304c\u5831\u9053|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201811150000154.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=15 November 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It was announced on 29 December 2018 that he signed for Toulouse, signing a three\u2013year contract for a transfer fee of 3 million euros and becoming the first Japanese player to join the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toulouse : accord officiel pour le Japonais Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Toulouse-accord-officiel-pour-le-japonais-gen-shoji/972722|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=29 December 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Cinq choses \u00e0 savoir sur Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/cinq-choses-savoir-sur-gen-shoji,47817.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=5 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Upon joining the club, Shoji said he will do his best at Toulouse and learn the speak the French language as quickly as possible.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"En France, je vais faire de mon mieux\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-en-france-je-vais-faire-de-mon-mieux-,47772.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=1 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'ai l'intention d'apprendre le fran\u00e7ais le plus rapidement possible\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-ai-l-intention-d-apprendre-le-francais-le-plus-rapidement-possible-,47836.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=6 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nShoji made his Toulouse debut, starting the whole game and keeping a clean sheet, in a 1\u20130 win against [[N\u00eemes Olympique]] on 19 January 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ligue 1 : Toulouse se fait du bien \u00e0 N\u00eemes|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Toulouse-se-fait-du-bien-a-nimes/979381|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=19 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> He kept another clean sheet in a follow\u2013up match against [[Angers SCO]], as they drew 0\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ligue 1 : Toulouse et Angers dos \u00e0 dos|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ligue-1-toulouse-et-angers-dos-a-dos/982448|publisher=L\u2019Equipe|language=French|date=27 January 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Since joining the club, Shoji became a first team regular for the club, playing in the centre\u2013back position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"Je veux apporter mon esprit de comp\u00e9titeur, \u00e7a manquait un peu \u00e0 Toulouse\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-je-veux-apporter-mon-esprit-de-competiteur-ca-manquait-un-peu-a-toulouse-,48943.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=2 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=ASSE - TFC : La d\u00e9fense \u00e0 cinq sera reconduite|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/asse-tfc-la-defense-a-cinq-sera-reconduite,49235.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=28 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'ai une pr\u00e9f\u00e9rence pour un sch\u00e9ma \u00e0 deux d\u00e9fenseurs centraux, plut\u00f4t qu'\u00e0 trois\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-ai-une-preference-pour-un-schema-a-deux-defenseurs-centraux-plutot-qu-a-trois-,49382.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Manager [[Alain Casanova]] described Shoji\u2019s signings as a \"very good pick\" after watching his performance but expected him to improve.<ref>{{cite news|title=Casanova : \"Shoji, une tr\u00e8s bonne pioche de notre recrutement\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/casanova-shoji-une-tres-bonne-pioche-de-notre-recrutement-,48955.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=4 April 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Casanova : \"Shoji cherche \u00e0 s'am\u00e9liorer en permanence\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/casanova-shoji-cherche-a-s-ameliorer-en-permanence-,49383.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=9 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji was able to help to help the club avoid relegation despite bad results.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3082\u30bb\u30b9\u30af\u306b\uff36\u5f3e\u6d74\u3073\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u6557\u308c\u308b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201902030000032.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=3 February 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b5016\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3000\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30eb\u30fc\u30ba\u5f15\u304d\u5206\u3051|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201905120000080.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u79fb\u7c4d\u5f8c\u516818\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u30d5\u30eb\u51fa\u5834\u3000\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u9006\u8ee2\u8ca0\u3051|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201905250000088.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=25 May 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2018\u201319 season, he made twenty appearances in all competitions.\n\nAhead of the 2019\u201320 season, however, Shoji suffered a hamstring injury during a pre\u2013season match in a 1\u20130 defeat against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] and was sidelined for a month.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brest - TFC : Gen Shoji vers un forfait|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/brest-tfc-gen-shoji-vers-un-forfait,50320.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=7 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji absent plusieurs semaines?|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-absent-plusieurs-semaines-,50414.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=14 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=PSG - TFC : Gen Shoji toujours \u00e0 l'infirmerie|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/psg-tfc-gen-shoji-toujours-a-l-infirmerie,50533.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=24 August 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 6 September 2019 when he made his return from injury, appearing in a friendly match against [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite news|title=TFC 1-2 Athletic Bilbao : Les 3 choses \u00e0 retenir et les notes sur 10|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/tfc-1-2-athletic-bilbao-les-3-choses-a-retenir-et-les-notes-sur-10,50722.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=6 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It wasn\u2019t until on 25 September 2019 when Shoji made his first league appearance of the season and started the match, as Toulouse lost 2\u20130 against Angers SCO.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u4eca\u5b63\u521d\u5148\u767a\u3082\u8ca0\u50b7\u3067\u524d\u534a\u4ea4\u4ee3\u3000\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u306f\u6557\u308c\u308b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/world/news/201909260000013.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Shoji played 45 minutes, as he sprained his ankle and was substituted.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji victime d'une entorse|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-victime-d-une-entorse,50949.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=25 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> This turns out to be his only appearance for the club this season. Initially out for three weeks, Shoji was sidelined for months and never played for Toulouse again.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gen Shoji absent plusieurs semaines|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/gen-shoji-absent-plusieurs-semaines,50968.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=27 September 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji rechute, Sa\u00efd et Sangar\u00e9 incertains, le point sur l'infirmerie|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-rechute-said-et-sangare-incertains-le-point-sur-l-infirmerie,51516.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=8 November 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Bless\u00e9, Gen Shoji part au Japon se faire soigner|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/blesse-gen-shoji-part-au-japon-se-faire-soigner,51953.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=13 December 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> It was reported in late\u2013January that Toulouse accepted a bid from Gamba Osaka for Shoji.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : Une offre venue du Japon pour Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-une-offre-venue-du-japon-pour-gen-shoji,52542.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=Japanese|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Upon leaving the club, it was reported that Shoji wanted to leave the club, having failed to settle in France and later stated it was a difficult decision to leave.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : C'est Shoji qui a envie de partir|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-c-est-shoji-qui-a-envie-de-partir,52547.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Shoji : \"J'\u00e9tais perdu \u00e0 Toulouse, mais c'\u00e9tait une d\u00e9cision difficile de partir\"|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/shoji-j-etais-perdu-a-toulouse-mais-c-etait-une-decision-difficile-de-partir-,52717.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=10 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Toulouse. Gen Shoji, entre culpabilit\u00e9 et mal du pays|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/02/05/gen-shoji-entre-culpabilite-et-mal-du-pays,8711438.php|publisher=La Depeche|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Gamba Osaka===\nIt was announced on 3 February 2020 that [[Gamba Osaka]] signed Shoji on a five\u2013year contract for a reported transfer fee of 850,000 euros.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mercato : La presse japonaise d\u00e9voile le prix du transfert de Gen Shoji|url=https://www.lesviolets.com/actu/mercato-la-presse-japonaise-devoile-le-prix-du-transfert-de-gen-shoji,52609.html|publisher=Les Violets|language=French|date=5 February 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/10810/|title=\u660c\u5b50 \u6e90\u9078\u624b \u30ac\u30f3\u30d0\u5927\u962a\u3078\u5b8c\u5168\u79fb\u7c4d\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|publisher=Gamba Osaka|language=Japanese|date=31 January 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194636/https://www.gamba-osaka.net/news/index/no/10810/|archivedate=28 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Gen Shoji.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Shoji trying to defend the ball from [[Romelu Lukaku]] during a quarter\u2013final match in the World Cup against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] on 2 July 2018.]]\n\nIt was announced on 1 October 2014 that Shoji was called up for the [[Japan national football team|Japan]]\u2019s squad for the first time by Manager [[Javier Aguirre]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u306b\u9999\u5ddd\u3089\u5fa9\u5e30!!\u5c0f\u6797\u60a0\u3001\u5869\u8c37\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u521d\u9078\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?148423-148423-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=1 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he withdrew from the squad, due to an injury.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9e7f\u5cf6\u660c\u5b50\u3001\u53f3\u592a\u3082\u3082\u88cf\u8ca0\u50b7\u3067\u4ee3\u8868\u8f9e\u9000|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/f-sc-tp2-20141005-1377979.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 October 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Two months later, it was announced that Shoji was called up for the national team ahead of the [[2015 AFC Asian Cup|AFC Asian Cup]] in [[Australia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u676f\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc23\u4eba\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a!!\u6e05\u6b66\u304cW\u676f\u4ee5\u6765\u306e\u5fa9\u5e30\u3067\u30a2\u30ae\u30fc\u30ecJ\u521d\u62db\u96c6|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?153584-153584-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=15 December 2014|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, he appeared as an unused substitute throughout the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u6307\u5c0e\u3057\u3066\u3082\u3089\u3063\u305f\u3053\u3068\u5fd8\u308c\u306a\u3044\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/p-sc-tp2-20150205-1430529.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=5 February 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=UAE\u6226\u3078\u68ee\u91cd\u3082\u5148\u767a\u30014\u8a66\u5408\u9023\u7d9a\u3067\u30b9\u30bf\u30e1\u30f3\u306b\u5909\u66f4\u306a\u3057|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?156085-156085-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u4ee3\u8868\u6563\u6b69\u968a\u306e\u30c6\u30fc\u30de\u306f\u300c\u690d\u7530\u306e\u5fc3\u3092\u958b\u3053\u3046\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?155827-155827-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIt wasn\u2019t until on 31 March 2015 when Shoji made his Japan debut against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]] in a friendly match, starting the whole game, as he helped the side beat Uzbekistan 5\u20131.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4ee3\u8868\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u306f\u9e7f\u5cf6\u3068\u306e\u9055\u3044\u306b\u3084\u3084\u6238\u60d1\u3044\u3082\u2026 |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?160005-160005-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=31 March 2015|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> A year later on 3 June 2016, Shoji made another appearance for Japan, coming on as the 84th minute substitute, in a 7\u20132 win against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u9999\u5ddd2\u767a!\u9ebb\u4e5f2\u767a!\u9577\u53cb\u30a2\u30b7\u30b9\u30c8\u306b\u6d45\u91ce\u3082\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\u30cf\u30ea\u30ebJ\u304c7\u767a\u5927\u52dd|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?190934-190934-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> In December 2017, he was called up to the national team squad for the [[2017 EAFF E-1 Football Championship|EAFF E-1 Football Championship]] as a host.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uff27\u5927\u962a\u521d\u702c\u3001\u9e7f\u5cf6\u4e09\u7aff\u3089\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\uff25\uff0d\uff11\u9078\u624b\u6a29\u4ee3\u8868|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201711290000056.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji captained Japan for the first time in his career and led the side to beat [[North Korea national football team|North Korea]] 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u660c\u5b50\u6e90\u300c\u6210\u9577\u3067\u304d\u305f\u300d\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\u521d\u4e3b\u5c06\u3067\u7121\u5931\u70b9\u52dd\u5229|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201712090000729.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=9 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> In a follow\u2013up match against [[China national football team|China]], he scored his first Japan goal, which turns out to be a winning goal, in a 2\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u65e5\u672c\u304c\u4e2d\u56fd\u7834\u308b\u3000\u5c0f\u6797\u3001\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u4ee3\u8868\u521d\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201712120000706.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> However, Japan lost 4\u20131 to [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in a deciding match, which resulted in the opposition team becoming champions in the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u65e5\u672c\u306f4\u5931\u70b9\u6557\u6226\u2026\u97d3\u56fd\u79f0\u3048\u308b\u30cf\u30ea\u30eb\u3001\u5148\u5236\u5f8c\u306e\u30d7\u30ec\u30fc\u306b\u7d0d\u5f97\u3044\u304b\u305a\u300c\u306a\u305c\u305d\u3046\u306a\u3063\u305f\u306e\u304b\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?233611-233611-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=16 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> After the match, Shoji reflected on the loss, saying: \"Today, Korea was amazing. There were a lot of things we had to follow. Of course, duels and balls, but it was quick to make blocks. It was ambiguous about today. I think it was a sad game.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5b88\u5099\u5d29\u58ca\u2026\u5c48\u8fb14\u5931\u70b9\u306b\u30ad\u30e3\u30d7\u30c6\u30f3\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u60c5\u3051\u306a\u3044\u8a66\u5408\u3060\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?233627-233627-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=17 December 2017|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, Shoji was named in Japan's preliminary [[Japan national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u897f\u91ceJ\u59cb\u52d5\u3078\u2026W\u676f\u6700\u7d42\u5019\u88dc27\u4eba\u306b\u672c\u7530\u3001\u9999\u5ddd\u3089\u3092\u9078\u51fa!!\u9752\u5c71\u304c\u30b5\u30d7\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?245043-245043-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Eventually, he made it to the final cut of the 23 men squad.<ref>{{cite news |script-title=ja:\u9152\u4e95\u5b8f\u6a39\u30012\u5ea6\u76ee\u306eW\u676f\u306b\u610f\u6c17\u8fbc\u3080\u300c\u3053\u306e4\u5e74\u9593\u78e8\u304d\u4e0a\u3052\u305f\u3082\u306e\u3092\u2026\u300d|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2018/05/31/post272190/|publisher=Football Channel Website|language=Japanese|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u897f\u91ce\u76e3\u7763\u306e\u65b0\u6226\u8853\u300c\uff13\uff0d\uff14\uff0d\uff13\u300d\u9577\u8c37\u90e8\u304c\uff23\uff22\u306b|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201805260000796.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=26 May 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji made his World Cup debut against [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in Matchday 1 of the Group Stage, where he played the whole game, in a 2-1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=World Cup: Japan beat 10-man Colombia in Group H|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439048|publisher=BBC Sport|date=19 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shoji later made two more starts in the tournament, as they were eliminated by [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the knockout stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u521d\u51fa\u5834\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u300c10\u4eba\u306a\u306e\u304b\u3068\u601d\u3046\u3050\u3089\u3044\u306e\u5727\u529b\u300d|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/russia2018/news/201806200000204.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=20 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u72d9\u308f\u308c\u305f\u660c\u5b50!? \u300c\u3042\u3063\u3001\u4ffa\u3060\u306a\u3068\u5206\u304b\u3063\u305f\u300d|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248102-248102-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=25 June 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u307f\u3093\u306a\u3067\u63a1\u70b9!!8\u5f37\u306b\u6311\u3093\u3060\u30d9\u30eb\u30ae\u30fc\u6226\u3001\u6700\u3082\u8a55\u4fa1\u304c\u9ad8\u304b\u3063\u305f\u306e\u306f\u2026|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?248835-248835-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=3 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Shortly after, [[Fox Sports]] named Shoji in the Asian\u2019s Best Eleven of the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u300c\u30b5\u30e0\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u3067\u6700\u9ad8\u306e\u30d1\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30de\u30f3\u30b9\u300d\u3001\u6d77\u5916\u30e1\u30c7\u30a3\u30a2\u304cW\u676f\u30a2\u30b8\u30a2\u30d9\u30b9\u30c811\u3092\u9078\u51fa|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?249070-249070-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the tournament, Shoji didn\u2019t receive a call up from the national team until March 2019 for a match against Colombia, which he played against and the side lost 1\u20130 on 22 March 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u4ee3\u8868\u5fa9\u5e30\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u304c\u4e00\u756a\u4e57\u308a\u3067\u5e30\u56fd\u3000\u300c\u697d\u3057\u307f\u300d\u3068\u7b11\u9854|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201903170000144.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=17 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u524d\u534a\u306e\u597d\u6a5f\u751f\u304b\u305b\u305aPK\u306b\u6c88\u3080\u2026\u68ee\u4fddJ\u3001\u30b3\u30ed\u30f3\u30d3\u30a2\u306b0-1\u6557\u6226|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?269432-269432-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=22 March 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Three months later in June, Shoji started two more matches back to back for the national side, including being a captain against [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] on 9 June 2019 and helping them kept two clean sheets.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u76f8\u624bGK\u304c\u597d\u5b88\u9023\u767a\u20263\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u521d\u63a1\u7528\u306e\u68ee\u4fddJ\u306f\u521d\u306e\u30b9\u30b3\u30a2\u30ec\u30b9\u30c9\u30ed\u30fc|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?276299-276299-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=Japanese|date=5 June 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=\u521d\u4e3b\u5c06\u306e\u660c\u5b50\u300c\u58f0\u901a\u3063\u3066\u304f\u308c\u305f\u300d\uff13\u30d0\u30c3\u30af\u7d71\u7387\u3067\uff10\u5c01|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201906090001135.html|publisher=Nikkan Sports|language=Japanese|date=9 June 2019|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{Updated|1 July 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway}}</ref><ref>Nippon Sports Kikaku Publishing inc./\u65e5\u672c\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u4f01\u753b\u51fa\u7248\u793e, [https://www.amazon.co.jp/2016J1-J2-J3%E9%81%B8%E6%89%8B%E5%90%8D%E9%91%91-NSK-MOOK/dp/4905411335/ref=pd_cp_14_1?ie=UTF8&refRID=1N6B11BBGDQ32GYF7MWJ \"2016J1&J2&J3\u9078\u624b\u540d\u9451\"], 10 February 2016, Japan, {{ISBN|978-4905411338}} (p. 42 out of 289)</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other<sup>[[#notes gs1|1]]</sup>\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"|[[Kashima Antlers]]\n|[[2011 J. League Division 1|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[J. League Division 1]]\n|0||0||2||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||2||0\n|-\n|[[2012 J. League Division 1|2012]]\n|9||0||4||1||5||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||18||1\n|-\n|[[2013 J. League Division 1|2013]]\n|4||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||5||0\n|-\n|[[2014 J. League Division 1|2014]]\n|34||2||0||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||0||0||40