s sold to [[Meralco|Manila Electric Company]] on August 2010.\n\n==Key dates==\n*'''August 29''': The [[2010 PBA Draft]] took place in [[Fort Bonifacio]], [[Taguig City]].\n\n==Draft picks==\n{{main|2010 PBA Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable sortable\"\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"10%\"| Round\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"10%\"| Pick\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"20%\"| Player\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"15%\"| Height\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"15%\"| Position\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"15%\"| Nationality\n! style=\"background:#fe5a12; color:white\" width=\"20%\"| College\n|- style=\"text-align: center\"\n| 1\n| 9\n| [[Shawn Weinstein]]\n|\n|\n| {{USA}}\n| [[St. Edwards University|St. Edwards]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center\"\n| 2\n| 11\n| [[Riego Gamalinda]]\n|\n|\n| {{PHI}}\n| [[San Beda College|San Beda]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center\"\n| 2\n| 14\n| [[Ford Arao]]\n|\n|\n| {{PHI}}\n| [[Ateneo de Manila University|Ateneo]]\n|- style=\"text-align: center\"\n| 2\n| 16\n| [[Khasim Mirza]]\n|\n|\n| {{PHI}}\n| [[University of Santo Tomas|UST]]\n|}\n\n==Roster==\n{{PBA roster header|team=Meralco Bolts\n| bg1 = #f47b34 | color1 = white\n| bg2 = #00005A | color2 = white\n}}\n<!--Using system used by the PBA: flag = country of birth place. this is the system used to classify filipino foreigners. If we'd go to the principle of they are all Filipinos, let's just remove the flag column.-->\n<!-- begin player list -->\n{{player2 | num = 2 | first = Chris | last = Timberlake | pos = PG | ft = 5 | in = 10 | lbs = 182 | college = [[University of North Florida|North Florida]] | nat = USA }}\n{{player2 | num = 3 | first = Solomon | last = Mercado | pos = PG | ft = 6 | in = 1 | lbs = 190 | college = [[Biola University]] | nat = PHI }}\n{{player2 | num = 4 | first = Renren | last = Ritualo | pos = G | ft = 6 | in = 2 | lbs = 178 | 