{"title_page": "John Burke (artist)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name        = John Burke\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  = 11 May 1946<ref name=grove>{{Cite web |last=Pyle |first=Hilary |title=Burke, John |url=https://doi.org/10.1093/gao/9781884446054.article.T012426 |work=[[Grove Art Online]] |publisher=Oxford University Press |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| death_date  = 11 Dec 2006<ref name=TimesObit>{{Cite news |title=Influential Irish sculptor and dedicated teacher of art |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/influential-irish-sculptor-and-dedicated-teacher-of-art-1.1042010 |newspaper=The Irish Times |date=2006-12-23 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Clonmel]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]<ref name=TimesObit/>\n| nationality = Irish\n| field       = \n| training    = \n| movement    =\n| works       = \n| patrons     =\n| awards      = \n}}\n\n'''John Burke''' (11 May 1946 &ndash; 11 December 2006) was an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[sculptor]].\n\nBurke studied at the [[Cork Institute of Technology|Crawford School of Art and Design]] in [[Cork (city)|Cork]] and at the [[Royal Academy of London]].<ref name=IMMA/> He spent most of his career in the Cork area<ref name=buried>{{Cite news |last=English |first=Eoin |title=Artist buried with back to adopted city |url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/artist-buried-with-back-to-adopted-city-20746.html |newspaper=Irish Examiner |date=2006-12-14 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref> and for a time taught at Crawford, where his students included [[Eilis O'Connell]] and [[Vivienne Roche]].<ref name=IMMA/>\n\nBurke was a founding member of [[Aosd\u00e1na]] in 1981.<ref name=TimesObit/><ref name=CallsToRepair>{{Cite news |last=McNamara |first=Robert |title=Calls to repair steel sculpture on Wilton Roundabout  |url=https://www.echolive.ie/corknews/Calls-to-repair-steel-sculpture-on-Wilton-Roundabout-54a58467-ad89-42f4-bbd0-ee6aa0e958c9-ds |newspaper=The Echo |location=Cork |date=2019-12-13 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Etsumi'' (1973, Belfast, Ulster Mus.)<ref name=IMMA>{{Cite web |title=John Burke (1964-2006) |url=https://imma.ie/artists/john-burke/ |series=Collection Artists |publisher=Irish Museum of Modern Art |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210185256/https://imma.ie/artists/john-burke/ |archivedate=2019-12-10 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n* ''Red Cardinal'' (1978, Dublin, [[Miesian Plaza|Bank of Ireland Headquarters]])<ref name=Dublin50>{{Cite book |last=Dargan |first=Pat |title=Dublin in 50 Buildings |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=LTBDDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT138 |publisher=Amberley Publishing Limited |date=2017-11-15 |page=138 |isbn=9781445677743 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burke, John}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[[Category:2006 deaths]]\n[[Category:Irish sculptors]]\n[[Category:Aosd\u00e1na members]]\n[[Category:People from County Tipperary]]\n[[Category:20th-century Irish sculptors]]\n\n\n{{Ireland-sculptor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox artist\n| name        = John Burke\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  = 11 May 1946<ref name=grove>{{Cite web |last=Pyle |first=Hilary |title=Burke, John |url=https://doi.org/10.1093/gao/9781884446054.article.T012426 |publisher=Grove Art Online |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| death_date  = 11 Dec 2006<ref name=TimesObit>{{Cite news |title=Influential Irish sculptor and dedicated teacher of art |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/influential-irish-sculptor-and-dedicated-teacher-of-art-1.1042010 |newspaper=The Irish Times |date=2006-12-23 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Clonmel]], [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]<ref name=TimesObit/>\n| nationality = Irish\n| field       = \n| training    = \n| movement    =\n| works       = \n| patrons     =\n| awards      = \n}}\n\n'''John Burke''' (11 May 1946 &ndash; 11 December 2006) was an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[sculptor]].\n\nBurke studied at the [[Cork Institute of Technology|Crawford School of Art and Design]] in [[Cork (city)|Cork]] and at the [[Royal Academy of London]].<ref name=IMMA/> He spent most of his career in the Cork area<ref name=buried>{{Cite news |last=English |first=Eoin |title=Artist buried with back to adopted city |url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/ireland/artist-buried-with-back-to-adopted-city-20746.html |newspaper=Irish Examiner |date=2006-12-14 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref> and for a time taught at Crawford, where his students included [[Eilis O'Connell]] and [[Vivienne Roche]].<ref name=IMMA/>\n\nBurke was a founding member of [[Aosd\u00e1na]] in 1981.<ref name=TimesObit/><ref name=CallsToRepair>{{Cite news |last=McNamara |first=Robert |title=Calls to repair steel sculpture on Wilton Roundabout  |url=https://www.echolive.ie/corknews/Calls-to-repair-steel-sculpture-on-Wilton-Roundabout-54a58467-ad89-42f4-bbd0-ee6aa0e958c9-ds |newspaper=The Echo |location=Cork |date=2019-12-13 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Etsumi'' (1973, Belfast, Ulster Mus.)<ref name=IMMA>{{Cite web |title=John Burke (1964-2006) |url=https://imma.ie/artists/john-burke/ |series=Collection Artists |publisher=Irish Museum of Modern Art |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210185256/https://imma.ie/artists/john-burke/ |archivedate=2019-12-10 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n* ''Red Cardinal'' (1978, Dublin, [[Miesian Plaza|Bank of Ireland Headquarters]])<ref name=Dublin50>{{Cite book |last=Dargan |first=Pat |title=Dublin in 50 Buildings |url=https://books.google.ie/books?id=LTBDDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT138 |publisher=Amberley Publishing Limited |date=2017-11-15 |page=138 |isbn=9781445677743 |accessdate=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burke, John}}\n[[Category:1946 births]]\n[